<BLOCKQUOTE><H2><FONT SIZE="+1" COLOR="990000">CONSERVING NATURE AND NATURAL
RESOURCES</FONT></H2>
<H3><I><B>This section covers principles three, four and five of the WMX
Environmental Policy through which WMX conserves nature  and natural resources:
conserving wetlands and biodiversity,  buying recycled products, and generating
and saving energy.</B></I></H3></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P><SMALL><B>Principle 3: Biodiversity</B><BR>The Company is
committed to the conservation of nature.  We will implement a policy of a &quot;no
net loss&quot; of wetlands or other biological diversity on the Company's
property.</SMALL></P>
<P><SMALL><B>Principle 4: Sustainable Use of Natural Resources</B><BR>The
Company will use renewable natural resources, such as water, soils and forests,
in a sustainable manner and will offer services to make degraded resources once
again usable.  We will conserve nonrenewable natural resources through efficient
use and careful planning.</SMALL></P>
<P><SMALL><B>Principle 5: Wise Use of Energy</B><BR>The Company will make
every reasonable effort to use environmentally safe and suitable energy sources
to meet our needs.  We will seek opportunities to improve energy efficiency and
conservation in our operations.</SMALL></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<CENTER><TABLE ALIGN="CENTER"><TR><TD COLSTART="1"><IMG
ALIGN="MIDDLE" SRC="./art/report/pr15.gif" ALT="Conserving Nature and Natural Resources"></TD></TR>
