<BLOCKQUOTE><H2><FONT SIZE="+1" COLOR="990000">ACCOUNTABILITY</FONT></H2>
<H3><I><B>This section covers four programs implementing principles eight, 13
and 14 of the WMX Environmental Policy through which WMX  is accountable to its
shareholders and the public: remediation at WMX facilities, management
accountability and employee involvement, environmental certifications and public
disclosure through the Annual Environmental Report.</B></I></H3></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P><SMALL><B>Principle 13: Environmental Policy Assessment</B><BR>The
Board of Directors of the Company will evaluate and will address the
environmental implications of its decisions. The Executive Environmental
Committee of the Company will report directly to the Chief Executive Officer of
the Company and will monitor and report upon implementation of this policy and
other environmental matters. The Company will commit the resources needed to
implement these principles. </SMALL></P>
<P><SMALL><B>Principle 14: Annual Environmental Report</B><BR>The Company
will prepare and make public an annual report on its environmental activities.
The report will include a self-evaluation of the Company's implementation of
these principles, including an assessment of the Company's performance in
complying with all applicable environmental laws and regulations throughout its
worldwide operations.</SMALL></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE><CENTER><IMG SRC="./art/report/pr21.gif" ALT="Accountability"></CENTER>
<P><SMALL>1 Including programs to assess and respond to potential remediation
responsibilities, does not necessarily mean that business units have been named
PRP's</SMALL></P>
<CENTER><P>For further explanation of this chart <A HREF="pg2.htm">CLICK
HERE!</A></P></CENTER></BLOCKQUOTE>       
