<BLOCKQUOTE><H2><FONT COLOR="#990000"><FONT SIZE="4">British Facilities
Certified to Environmental Management Standard</FONT></FONT></H2>
<P><B><I>WMI plc's UK Waste has become the first company in the waste
management sector to have two of its landfills certified under the British
Environmental Management Standard known as BS 7750.</I></B></P>
<P></P>
<P><B><I>The Green Road Landfill in Ballyclare, one of the facilities
certified, has been operational for four years and was the first landfill in
Northern Ireland to be engineered with a double layer liner of synthetic and
natural materials. The other facility, the Windmill Quarry Landfill in
Washington, West Sussex, accepts domestic waste from East and West Sussex along
with industrial and commercial waste.</I></B></P>
<P><B><I> The BS 7750 standard establishes requirements for environmental
management systems and procedures. An independent, accredited assessor must
certify that the facility meets the standard, follows the procedures and is
committed to continual environmental performance.</I></B></P>
<P><B><I>intrinsically linked to environmental protection. All of UK Waste
recycling, treatment and disposal facilities are part of a rolling program to
obtain the BS 7750 accreditation.</I></B></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<CENTER></CENTER>
