<BLOCKQUOTE><H2><FONT SIZE="+1" COLOR="990000">LEADERSHIP</FONT></H2>
<H3><I><B>This section covers principles nine, 10, 11 and 12 of the WMX 
Environmental Policy through which WMX has committed to lead by example and
through partnerships with other organizations: research and development,
community involvement, environmental education, public policy development and
cooperation with environmental organizations.</B></I></H3></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P><SMALL><B>Principle 9: Research and Development</B><BR>The
Company will research, develop and implement technologies for integrated waste
management.</SMALL></P>
<P><SMALL><B>Principle 10: Public Education</B><BR>The Company will provide
information to and will assist the public in understanding the environmental
impacts of our activities.  We will conduct public tours of  facilities,
consistent with safety requirements, and will work with communities near our
facilities to encourage dialogue and exchange of information on facility
activities.</SMALL></P>
<P><SMALL><B>Principle 11: Public Policy</B><BR>The Company will support and
participate in development of public policy and in educational initiatives that
will protect human health and improve the environment.  We will seek cooperation
on this work with government, environmental groups, schools, universities, and
other public organizations.</SMALL></P>
<P><SMALL><B>Principle 12: Participation in Environmental Organizations</B><BR>The
Company will encourage its employees to participate in and to support the work
of environmental organizations,  and we will provide support to environmental
organizations for the advancement of environmental protection.</SMALL></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE><CENTER><IMG
ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="./art/report/pr25.gif" ALT="Leadership"><BR><SMALL>1 In
this section, the implementation rating primarily reflects the presence or
absence of programs addressing these issues.  Few objective standards exist to
rate the adequacy of these programs.</SMALL></CENTER></BLOCKQUOTE>
