<H2><FONT COLOR="#990000"><FONT SIZE="4">GETTING SMART ABOUT RECYCLING</FONT></FONT></H2>
<P><B><I>Waste Management's Davis Street Station for Material Recycling and
Transfer (SMaRT) facility in San Leandro, California has long been recognized
for its innovative recycling programs. Now it is also home to an innovative
environmental education center.</I></B></P>
<P><B><I>In partnership with the City of San Leandro, WMI built a $150,000
education center at the SMaRT facility. The center features seven museum-quality
interactive exhibits. These illustrate the four R's - Reduce, Reuse, Recycle and
Rot (compost); 'closing the loop' by using recycled products; the history of
garbage; and landfill disposal. A full-time educator gives tours of the center
and works with school groups. The tours are supplemented by in-classroom
instructional materials developed by local environmental educators.</I></B></P>
<P><B><I>Since its opening in mid-1995, more than 2,000 people have
participated in educational programs at the center.</I></B></P>
<CENTER><IMG ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="./art/report/ribbon.gif" ALT="Ribbon Cutting"></CENTER>
