<HEAD>

<TITLE>WMX - Recycling In Full Swing</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Web Builder, 16-May-1995 -->

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.00">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Don Grage">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Don Grage">
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<H2>Recycling In Full Swing</H2>
<HR SIZE=5>

<IMG SRC="../art/report/truck.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10 ALT="[IMAGE: A Recycling Truck entering the Davis Street SMaRT, Oakland, CA]">

Where can you recycle a pair of Levis, an old mattress, carpet padding
and a toilet?  At WMX's Davis Street Station for Material Recycling
and Transfer (SMaRT) in Oakland, California.  Located at California's
largest transfer station, the SMaRT center offers buyback and dropoff
recycling services for an extensive and exotic list of items,
totalling more than 54,000 tons in 1994.  In addition, a Salvation
Army donation trailer at the center recovered more than 220 tons of
reusable items. The center also pioneered a service agreement with
Appliance Recycling Centers of America.  WMI's commitment to provide
thousands of used appliances allowed the company to locate a new plant
in Oakland that will employ 29 technicians when it reaches full
capacity.

<P>
With support from the Alameda County Waste Management Authority, SMaRT
is developing an education center with displays on recycling and
integrated waste management.  And, to round out the year in recycling,
SMaRT managed the demolition of one of its own buildings, a
Depression-era structure.  More than 60 percent of the material was
recycled, including 37 truckloads of concrete and masonry and 11 loads
of steel.

<P><HR>
<H5><CENTER>
<A HREF="http://www.wmx.com/">WMX Main Level</A> ||
