<HEAD>

<TITLE>WMX - Process Improvement Brings Environmental Benefits</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Web Builder, 15-May-1995 -->

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.00">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Don Grage">
<META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="Don Grage">
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<H2>Process Improvement Brings Environmental Benefits</H2>
<HR SIZE=5>

An important tool of WMX's quality program is process improvement.
Cross-functional teams are formed around key business issues with the
goal of analyzing existing processes and recommending "breakthrough"
improvements.

<P>
Several teams have examined and made recommendations about
environmental processes, including the Compliance Management System
and the environmental audit program.  Implementing the recommendations
is making these key programs more consistent, useful and efficient.
Less obvious are the environmental benefits to be gained by examining
business processes with an eye toward costs.  For example, a 1994 team
recommended changes to commercial routing procedures that could
decrease the miles driven by 20 percent -- with corresponding savings
in fuel consumption and air pollution.  Another team recommended
changes to the tire maintenance program that will improve safety and
reduce the number of tires scrapped.

<P>
A team also reviewed the Annual Environmental Report.  After talking
to many users of the report internally and externally, the team
recommended printing a streamlined report for widespread use by those
who want an overview of the Company's environmental progress, putting
the report on the Internet and preparing a more detailed report for
those wanting further information.  The more detailed report is
available primarily on disk.  This approach has cut the number of
printed pages by two-thirds.  Reproduction onto a disk can be done on
demand, eliminating the potential for excess inventory and waste.

<P><HR>
<H5><CENTER>
<A HREF="http://www.wmx.com/">WMX Main Level</A> ||
<A HREF="report-intro.html#toc">Table of Contents</A> ||
