</head>
         <CENTER>SECRETARY,  MARITIME ADMINISTRATION AND MARITIME SUBSIDY BOARD</CENTER><P>
<OL>                    
     <LI TYPE=1><B>Mission.</B> To develop, coordinate, and direct administrative,
         legal, and management aspects of Maritime Administration
         policies and programs.<P>
         
     <LI><B>Functions.</B>  Under the general direction and supervision of the
         Administrator or the Maritime Subsidy Board, the Secretary,
         Maritime Administration and Maritime Subsidy Board shall:<P>
        <OL>
     <LI TYPE=a> Direct correspondence and documents received by the office
         to the officials concerned providing direction consistent
         with the policy of the Maritime Administrator and the
         Maritime Subsidy Board.<P>
         
     <LI>Prepare briefing or informational papers, final opinions,
         decisions, and orders deemed necessary; arrange hearings,
         meetings, and conferences involving the Maritime Subsidy
         Board; serve, as required, as an alternate member of the
         Board in the event of a vacancy or absence or disability of
         a member; and coordinate ongoing strategic analysis of
         problems faced by the maritime industry.<P>
         
     <LI>Arrange for the services of Administrative Law Judges
         (ALJs), as required, to meet the Maritime Administration
         needs and provide administrative support for retained ALJs.
         Obtain all statements of expense and compensation for
         representation before the Maritime Administration or the
         Maritime Subsidy Board.<P>
         
     <LI>Supervise bid openings for ship construction or sale and
         insurance.<P>
         
     <LI>Issue certifications/certificates, administer oaths, affix
         seals, sign or execute contracts/aqreements, and maintain
         files of actions and petitions.<P>
        </OL>         
</OL>
