<html>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>U.S. MARITIME ADMINISTRATION</TITLE>

<!pn=omlt.htm/page edited on 12/4/96blh->
<!Office of Maritime, Labor, Training and Safety->
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="OMLT.GIF"></CENTER>
<P>
     
<CENTER>OFFICE OF MARITIME LABOR, TRAINING, AND SAFETY</CENTER>
<P>
                    
<B>Mission. </B>  To analyze and advise theMaritime Administrator
       regarding labor management relations and problems, training, and
       safety as they apply to seafaring, longshore, and shipyard
       workers.<P>
         
<B>Functions. </B> Under the general direction and supervision of the
         Maritime Administrator, the Director, Office of Maritime Labor,
         Training, and Safety shall:<P>
       <OL>  
        <LI TYPE=a> Direct studies and supervise development and 
         dissemination
         of reports on all areas of organized maritime labor.<p>
        <LI>Supervise development of plans to provide a reserve maritime 
         work force for mobilization and other emergencies.
         Determine the need for and coordinate training programs for
         licensed and unlicensed personnel in maritime industries.<P>
         
        <LI>Process nominations for appointments to the U.S. Merchant
         Marine Academy and conduct related congressional liaison.
         Certify eligibility and issue or arrange for issuance of
         merchant marine decorations and awards.<P>
         
        <LI>Administer an assistance program for the state maritime
         academies.  Coordinate technical maritime training
         assistance to foreign countries under international
         agreements.<P>
         
        <LI>Promote the use of safe practices in the maritime industry
         and provision of high quality safety training at the United
         States Merchant Marine Academy, state maritime academies,
         and maritime industry schools.<P>
        </OL>         
<P>
<HR>
<hr>
<p>
</BODY>
