<p>
<a><h4><center>OFFICE OF THE ASSOCIATE ADMINISTRATOR<br>
NATIONAL SECURITY</A></CENTER></h4>
<P>

<B>Mission. </B> To implement and administerthe Maritime Security
         Program for assisting and maintaining a U.S. flag merchant fleet
         to serve both the commercial and national security needs of the
         United States, formulate national policies and programs for
         operation, maintenance, and repair of administration-owned or
         acquired ships, and maintain liaison with Department of Defense
         officials on related matters.<P>
         
<B>Functions. </B> Under the general direction and supervision of the
         Maritime Administrator, the Associate Administrator for National
         Security shall provide executive direction over the following
         organizations:<P>
  

<P>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="AA31.htm"><IMG SRC="AA31.GIF"></A>
<A HREF="AA32.htm"><IMG SRC="AA32.GIF"></A>
