<IMG SRC="usa_line.gif"><center><H1>VESSEL SERVICE GUIDE</H1>



                <H2>SUPPORT AMERICA - SHIP U.S. FLAG</H2> 


<H3><A HREF="#U.S. carrier">SUPPORT U.S.-FLAG CARRIERS</A>
</H3></center><IMG SRC="usa_line.gif"><P>Statements by:<BR><A HREF="#Secquote">Secretary of Transportation</A><BR><A HREF="#Admquote">Maritime Administrator</A><BR><A HREF="#FMCquote">Chairman, Federal Maritime Commission</A><HR><A HREF="#Policy">Make It Your Policy, Too.</A><HR><A HREF="#Liner">U.S.-flag ocean carriers and their service routes</A><BR>U.S.-flag carrriers' <A HREF="#Foreign">service to foreign destinations.</A><BR><A HREF="#Domestic">Domestic shipping services</A><BR><A HREF="#Key to service type">Key to service type</A><BR><HR><A HREF="#Info">For further information</A><BR><A HREF="#Offices">MARAD Offices and Representatives<BR><A HREF="#Other">Other frequently used numbers </A>concerning ocean shipping<BR>MARAD help line: 1 800 9US-FLAG<BR>Computer bulletin board:  202 366-8505<BR>MARAD World Wide Web home page: <A HREF="newmarad.htm"><I>http://marad.dot.gov</I> </A><BR>Send <A HREF="MAILTO:marketing.marad@marad.dot.gov">e-mail </A>to MARAD's Office of Marketing<HR><A HREF="newmarad.htm">Return to home page</A><P><IMG SRC="/usa_line.gif"><BR><BR><BR><BR>
<P><BR><BR><BR><BR><A NAME="U.S. carrier"<H4><IMG SRC="/usa_line.gif"><P>The U.S. carrier</A> industry is vital to national defense and our international commerce.<BR><BR> American ships are the best guarantee of delivery of material and personnel to U.S. combat forces stationed outside the continental United States.<BR><BR>Peacetime commercial transport is equally important.  <BR><BR>U.S. carriers reduce our transport dependence on foreign countries, provide jobs for Americans, and improve our balance of payments.  <BR><BR>Aside from inventing containerization and doublestack trains, U.S. carriers have set the pace for development of large-scale, dependable international distribution systems.</H4><IMG SRC="/usa_line.gif"></DL><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>

<P><A NAME="Secquote"><H3><IMG SRC="/usa_line.gif"><BR><BR>"The U.S. maritime industry </A>provides significant benefit to the
U.S. economy.  Having a strong merchant marine provides jobs and
an income stream to the economy.  It also supports a maritime
infrastructure that includes an educational and training base
that is needed for national security..."

                              <P>The Secretary of Transportation<BR><BR><IMG SRC="/usa_line.gif"><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>

</H3>

<P><A NAME="Admquote"><H3><IMG SRC="/usa_line.gif"><P>"... adequate and reliable</A> U.S.-flag sealift capacity remains
indispensable to national security...95 percent of the total
cargo which supported allied forces in the Middle East went by
sea [Desert Shield/Desert Storm].  More than 80 percent of the
sealift cargo was carried on U.S.-flag ships...The key roles of
both the Ready Reserve Fleet and the private, U.S.-flag merchant
fleet have been clearly validated.  This is all too clear in time
of war, and too often forgotten in time of peace..."

                              <P>The Maritime Administrator</H3><BR><IMG SRC="/usa_line.gif"><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>

<P><A NAME="FMCquote"><BR><IMG SRC="/usa_line.gif"><H3><P>"...The United States' commercial trading</A> interests cannot be
secure or protected in a highly competitive global market if all
of its trade is dependent on foreign shipping lines for its
carriage . . . I have not yet seen a realistic alternative to U..S.-
flag vessels that provides comparable security . . . This issue
really is whether the U.S. can be secure in its ability to
control terms and conditions in its trading routes if it has no
merchant marine of its own . . . ."

                         <P>Chairman, Federal</A> Maritime Commission<BR><BR><IMG SRC="/usa_line.gif"><BR><BR><BR>
</H3><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>
<H3><A NAME="Policy"><IMG SRC="/usa_line.gif"><BR><P>MAKE IT YOUR POLICY</A>, TOO</H3>

<P><BR><BR><P>Make it your company policy to have good working relationships
with U.S. carriers and to offer them a share of your cargo.  Let
your ocean freight expenditures work for both you and our
country.  It makes good business sense, and it supports major
national objectives.

<P>The U.S.-flag carriers shown here will welcome
the opportunity to discuss your service requirements for
successful access to overseas markets and suppliers.<BR><BR><IMG SRC="/usa_line.gif"><BR><BR><BR>

<BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>
<A NAME="Key to service type"><IMG SRC="/usa_line.gif"><B><P>Key to Service Type:</B></A><BR>
<UL>
<LI>  (BB) Breakbulk<BR>        <LI>  (C) Containers (FCL/LCL)<BR>
<LI>  (L) LASH Barge<BR>        
<LI>  (LB) Landbridge<BR>
<LI>  (R) Reefer<BR>           <LI>  (RO) Roll-on/Roll-off<BR>
<LI>  (TB) Tug/Barge<BR>
</UL><IMG SRC="/usa_line.gif"><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>

