<BODY>
<CENTER><H2>TITLE XI CUSTOMER SERVICE PLAN</H2></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>Federal Ship Financing</CENTER>
<PRE>

Our Mission

*    Facilitate ongoing efforts to make U.S. shipyards
     internationally competitive

*    Participate aggressively in the conversion of U.S.
     shipyards from defense to commercial projects

*    Promote the growth and modernization of the U.S. maritime
     industries

The Federal Ship Financing Program Provides

*    A U.S. government guarantee of private sector debt
     financing

*    Fixed interest rates comparable to those available to
     large and financially strong corporations

*    Long-term amortization

*    Financing of up to 87.5% of a project's cost

Who We Serve

*    Vessel owners/operators

*    U.S. shipyards

*    Financial institutions

*    Maritime industry professionals

*    Other maritime-related industries

Services We Provide

*    We finance commercially viable projects and assume
     prudent risks

*    We provide program information through seminars and
     meetings, letters of interest, and brochures

*    We arrange pre-application meetings between applicants
     and Maritime Administration staff

*    We provide technical assistance for ensuring complete
     applications
                                                             
Our Commitment to You

*    We will evaluate the completeness of your application and
     provide you with an initial response within 10-14 days

*    We will return your phone calls within 24 hours

*    We will respond to your information requests within 1-
     3 days

*    We will provide you with status reports of your
     application progress on request

*    We will process a complete application within 60 days

*    We will treat you with respect and courtesy at all times


                 Customer Service Plan Update


*    How Well Have We Done Our Job ? 


     We have evaluated the six standards which comprise our
     commitment to you.  We have effectively met our
     commitments to you.  You have indicated that we have
     successfully fulfilled our commitments.

     We have met our overall goal of expediting our review of
     Title XI applications, with the large majority processed
     within the 60 day timeframe, a significant improvement
     from prior years.  We are continuing to refine our
     processing procedures. 



*    What Have We Done ?

     In fiscal year 1995, we approved 14 new applications for
     Title XI financing.  The total cost of these projects is
     about $500 million with a related guarantee is
     approximately $436.9 million.



*    What Have You Told Us ?  

     Avondale Industries and National Steel and Shipbuilding
     Company have each stated that, as a result of the
     modernization of their facilities, there will be cost
     savings for both and naval ship construction.

     Industry comments on the proposed changes to the Title XI
     regulations clearly support MARAD's efforts to improve
     our administrative procedures.


Highlights for 1994 and 1995

1)   The first ocean going export financing project.  The
     project involved the construction of 4 product tankers
     for Fleves Shipping Corporation at a cost of
     approximately $152 million.  This project is expected to
     support 500 jobs at Newport News Shipbuilding.  

2)   Shipyard modernization projects which totalled $46,320,00
     for Avondale Industries, Inc. and National Steel and
     Shipbuilding Company were approved.  

3)   The construction of 4 double-hulled product tankers for
     American Heavy Lift Shipping Company by Avondale
     Industries was approved.  The vessels will be the first
     U.S. flag tankers constructed for the domestic trade in
     over ten years.  They will fully comply with the Oil
     Pollution Act of 1990.  This project is expected to
     support 300 jobs at American Heavy Lift Shipping Company
     and 900 jobs at the shipyard, Avondale Industries.      

4)   We have proposed changes to our regulations to improve
     the processing of Title XI applications.  

Who to Contact

Headquarters:
     Director, Office of Ship Financing
     U.S. Department of Transportation
     Maritime Administration
     Room 8122
     400 7th Street, S.W.
     Washington, D.C.  20590
     Phone: (202) 366-5744
     Fax: (202) 366-7901
     Judy_Bowers@Postmaster2.dot.gov.

Western Region:
     211 Main Street
     Room 1112
     San Francisco, CA  94105
     Phone: (415) 744-3125

Central Region:
     365 Canal Street
     Suite 2590
     New Orleans, LA  70130
     Phone: (504) 589-6556

Great Lakes Region:
     2860 South River Road
     Suite 185
     Des Plaines, IL  60018
     Phone: (708) 298-4535

North Atlantic Region:
     26 Federal Plaza
     Room 3737
     New York, NY  10278
     Phone: (212) 264-1300

South Atlantic Region:
     7737 Hampton Boulevard
     Building 4D, Room 211
     Norfolk, VA  23505
     Phone: (804) 441-6393

Hours of Operation:
     8:30 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.
     Local Time
 
</PRE>
