<TITLE>MARLINESPIKE CUSTOMER SERVICE PLAN</title>

<!pn=planm.htm/page last edited on 10/7/96blh->
<!page called by hpms2.htm->

</head>
<BODY>
<CENTER>MARITIME EXCHANGE: CUSTOMER SERVICE PLAN</center>
<CENTER>FOR THE MARlinspike ELECTRONIC BULLETIN BOARD</center>        
<HR>
<CENTER>OUR COMMITMENT TO ELECTRONIC BULLETIN BOARD USERS</center>
<HR>
<PRE>
OUR MISSION

The Maritime Administration (MARAD) operates an electronic bulletin
board system, MARLINESPIKE, to disseminate timely maritime related
information in a user friendly manner.


INFORMATION WE PROVIDE

     * U.S. ocean transportation services and
       schedules
     * International business opportunities
     * Information on shipbuilding and repair, including:
         - Federal loan guarantees
         - Shipyard bulletins and news
         -  Shipbuilding technical information sharing
         - Research and development
         - Regulations and standards
         - Maritime technology (Maritech)
     * Public messages
     * MARAD acquisitions, solicitations, procurement plans,
       contract awards and small business opportunities
     * Current MARAD press release
     * Foreign assets control regulations    


WHO WE SERVE

Importers and Exporters
U.S-flag carriers
U.S. shipyards
Marine equipment and services vendors
Other industry professionals


ACCESS

Is This System Customer Friendly?

Yes! Use your personal computer and a modem to access the bulletin
board syste. Set your modem to 8 bits, no parity, 1 stop bit and 
dial (202)366-8505.
 
A help line also has been established to assist you with any 
technical problems or questions you may have about using the
bulletin board.  The help line (1-800-9US-FLAG) is manned
from 8:30 AM to 5:00 PM EST, Monday through Friday.

Can Users Provide Input and Submit Questions?

Yes! The board has an E-mail system.  In addition, many menus
contain a selection for user suggestions and questions.

Is There A Charge For This System?

No. This service is free, although local or long distance telephone
charges may apply.


OUR PLEDGE TO YOU

  ** We will maintain current and timely information.

  ** We will respond within 24 hours to any questions you may
     have about system operations.

  ** We will maintain system availability on a 24-hour basis.

  ** We will monitor the forum continuously to provide you
     with current maritime information.

  ** We will welcome any suggestions you may have on how we
     can improve this system through the E-mail selection
     found on the bulletin board or by calling our help line
     at 1-800-9US-FLAG.

  ** We will treat you with courtesy and respect at all times.


WHO TO CONTACT FOR PROGRAM INFORMATION

If you are unable to find the information you want on the
Marlinspike bulletin board, offices throughout the U.S. are
staffed with trade specialists to assist you in answering
any questions.

Headquarters:
     U.S. Department of Transportation
     Maritime Administration
     Office of Marketing , Room 7209
     Washington DC 20590
     Phone (202)366-5508   FAX(202)366-5522

Western Region:
     201 Mission St. Ste 2200
     San Francisco CA 94105
     Phone (415)744-3125   FAX(415)744-2576

Central Region:
     365 Canal Street Ste 2590
     New Orleans LA 70130
     Phone (504)589-6556   FAX(504)589-6559


Great Lakes Region:
     2860 South River Road Ste 185
     Des Plaines IL 60018
     Phone (708)298-4535   FAX(708)298-4537

North Atlantic Region:
     26 Federal Plaza Room 3737
     New York NY 10278
     Phone (212)264-1300   FAX(212)264-1958

South Atlantic Region:
     7737 Hampton Boulevard
     Building 4D Room 211
     Norfolk VA 23505
     Phone (804)441-6393   FAX(804)440-0812

                    Hours of Operation
                    8:30 am - 5:00 pm    
                        Local Time            

Ship Your Cargo On                          Build Your Ships In
U.S. FLAG SHIPS                                U.S. SHIPYARDS
<P>
</PRE>
