<BODY>
<CENTER>NATIONAL MARITIME RESOURCE & EDUCATION CENTER</CENTER>
<CENTER>CUSTOMER SERVICE PLAN</CENTER>
<HR><HR>
<PRE>
OUR MISSION

To support the efforts of U.S. shipbuilders, ship repairers, and
marine supplies to compete in the international commercial
marketplace by acting as a major information source and facilitator
for the maritime industry.


WHO WE SERVE

* U.S. Shipyards

* U.S. Ship Repair Yards

* U.S. Marine Suppliers

* Vessel Owners/Operators

* Maritime Industry Professionals

* Other Maritime-Related Interests


RESOURCES

* An extensive marine industry standards library.

* A Computer-Aided Design (CAD) library.

* Metric guideline specifications.

* International Organization for Standards (ISO) 9000
  information on quality assurance and management.

* ISO 14000 information on marine environmental protection.

* Experienced professional staff in all maritime disciplines.


SERVICES WE PROVIDE

* Response to inquiries.

* Electronic access to standards and CAD library files.

* Metrication assistance and referrals.

* Technical support and U.S. liaison to the 
  International Organization for Standards (ISO).

* Support for industry standards ISO 9000 and 
  ISO 14000 registration.

* Analysis and interpretation of current shipbuilding
  regulations, standards, and specifications.

* Dissemination of information through conferences,
  workshops, and seminars.


OUR COMMITMENT TO YOU

* We will provide accurate and complete responses
  to your inquiries.

* We will maintain an up-to-date standards and CAD Library.

* We will provide technical assistance in using all
  library resources.

* We will respond to your information requests within 1-3 days.

* We will return your telephone calls within 24 hours.

* We will treat you with respect and courtesy at all times.


PRIMARY POINTS OF CONTACT

Headquarters
   Director 
   Office of Shipyard Revitalization
   Maritime Administration
   U.S. Department of Transportation
   MAR-750, Room 7326
   400 Seventh Street, SW
   Washington, DC  20590
     Phone:(202)366-1931
       Fax:(202)366-7197

Hours of Operation: 8:30 a.m. - 5:00 p.m. EST

=============================================
MARLINSPIKE 24-Hour Bulletin Board System   
   Set modem to 8 bits, no parity, 
   1 stop bit and dial: (202) 366-8505
=============================================

