<HEAD>
<TITLE>USMMA CUSTOMER SERVICE PLAN</title>

<!pn=planu.htm/page last edited on 10/7/96blh->
<!page called by hpms2.htm->
</head>

<BODY>
<CENTER>UNITED STATES MERCHANT MARINE ACADEMY</CENTER>
<CENTER>CUSTOMER SERVICE PLAN</CENTER>
<HR><HR>
<PRE>
OUR MISSION

Educate and graduate officers and leaders of honor and integrity
who are dedicated to serving the economic and defense interests of
the United States in our Armed Forces and Merchant Marine, and who
will contribute to an intermodal transportation system that
effectively ties America together.


USMMA PROVIDES

* An accredited, four year college program focused on academic 
  excellence.

* A regimental program designed to foster leadership skills,
  teamwork and decision-making.

* A year of sea training on U.S.merchant ships with an opportunity 
  for hands-on experience and foreign travel. Tuition, room and 
  board, books, uniforms and medical coverage while in residence.

* A safe and scenic 82-acre waterside campus with modern facilities
  and state-of-the-art laboratories.


WHO WE SERVE

* Candidates who seek admission to the Academy.

* A diverse student population of some 950 college-age men and 
  women representing every state as well as U.S. territories and 
  possessions and foreign nations.

* The U.S. Armed Forces.

* Maritime companies and organizations who employ our graduates. 


SERVICES WE PROVIDE

* A curriculum leading to a Bachelor of Science degree, a   
  merchant marine officer's license, and a U.S. Naval
  Reserve commission.

* Majors in:

     * MarineTransportation
     * Marine Engineering  
     * Ship's Officer      
     * Dual License        
     * Marine Engineering Systems
     * Marine Engineering Management

* Small class size.

* An intercollegiate athletic program of 23 varsity sports and an 
  extensive intramural program.

* Exceptiona1 waterfront facilities.

* Student clubs, professional society chapters, social and cultural 
  activities.

* A Career Development office to assist in job placement.

* A Continuing Education program serving the training needs of the 
  maritime community.


OUR COMMITMENT TO YOU

* Evaluate all admissions applications fairly and base offers of  
  appointment on candidate merit.

* Provide information about an applicant's status within 24 hours 
  of a request.

* Notify applicants of selection for enrollment by May 1 if the   
  application is received by March 1.

* Maintain diversity in our student population and quality in our 
  educational program.

* Help you develop and sharpen your leadership skills.

* Provide information about our program within 24 hours of a
  request. 


WHO TO CONTACT   

U.S. Merchant Marine Academy
Steamboat Road              
Kings Point, N.Y. 11024-1699 


Admissions Office  
Out of NY State
800-732-6267

Admissions Office
New York residents 
516-773-5391

Public Information Office  
516-773-5374 (General Information)

Athletics Office
516-773-5454

Waterfront Center
516-773-5232

Group Tour Arrangements
516-773-5387

Continuing Education
516-773-5120

General Switchboard
516-773-5000 (For other offices)


Business Hours: 8 am - 4:30 pm, Monday - Friday

Campus Visiting Hours: 9 am - 5 pm, daily and weekends. 
Closed during July and on federal holidays.

IMPORTANT NOTE: Individuals who successfully complete the 
Academy's four year program incur a legal obligation after
graduation to serve in the U.S. Naval Reserve or another Armed
Forces reserve for eight years; to serve at sea aboard U.S.-flag
commercial vessel, or ashore in approved maritime-related
employment, or on active military duty, for five years; and to
maintain their merchant marine officer's license for at least six
years. 
</PRE>
