<BODY>
<CENTER>April 8, 1996</CENTER>
<CENTER>U.S. Department of Transportation</CENTER>
<CENTER>Maritime Administration</CENTER>
<CENTER>National Maritime Resource and Education Center</CENTER>
<CENTER>Marine Industry Standards Library</CENTER>
<P>

The purpose of the National Maritime Resource and Education Center's Marine
Industry Standards Library is to provide technical assistance to U.S. ship-
builders, ship repair facilities, and marine equipment suppliers in obtaining 
and using copies of domestic and international industry standards.  A 
technical staff is available to receive and investigate questions and assist 
the industry in the areas of standards, such as ASTM, ISO, and others listed 
below, and how they compare, relate, and their applications for shipbuilding 
and the marine industry. 
<P>
THE MARINE INDUSTRY STANDARDS LIBRARY HAS INFORMATION AVAILABLE BOTH
ON CD-ROM AND IN HARD COPY.
