<Body><P>

<center>NATIONAL MARITIME RESOURCE AND EDUCATION CENTER</center> 
<P>
<HR>
<HR>
<CENTER>Maritime Guideline Specifications for</center> 
<CENTER>Merchant Ship Construction, and its Executive Summary</center>
<HR>
<HR>
<P>
<CENTER>GUIDELINE SPECIFICATIONS STATUS INFORMATION</CENTER><BR>
<CENTER>April 1996</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>
    1)  The documents are guideline metric specifications intended to 
        provide guidance to the maritime industry for the preparation of 
        specifications for building competitive commercial ships in the 
        U.S. for domestic or export markets.  They each contain a total 
        of 73 sections; the first 29 sections comprise the Hull Sections, 
        and the remaining 44 sections comprise the Machinery Sections. 
<P>
    2)  Both documents have been reviewed and commented on by members 
        of the marine industry.
<P>
    3)  Both documents have been issued to the public. 
<P>
    4)  A limited number of hard copies of the documents are available
        for distribution to the public.  The Executive Summary contains
        132 pages, and the Guideline Specifications contains 461 pages.
        
To order a copy, in writing, send your request to:
<p>
Maritime Administration<p> 
Office of Shipyard Revitalization<p> 
MAR-750, Room 7326<p>
400 Seventh Street SW;<p> 
Washington, DC  20590-0001.
</P>
</P>
