<head>
<title>U.S. MARITIME ADMINISTRATION</title>
<!pn=ar2apenc.htm/page edited/implemented on 11-19-96blh->
<!page called by anrpt2m.htm->
<!info provider=BillDean->
<body>
<b>
<h3><center>APPENDIX-C: NEW MARITIME ADMINISTRATION REPORT ON<BR>  
U.S. PUBLIC PORT PROFITABILITY AND SELF-SUFFICIENCY</center></h3>
</b>
<p>
In fall 1996, MARAD will be publishing a new report, <i>Another Look at Public Port
Profitability and Self-Sufficiency</i>, which analyzes public port profitability from 1985 to 1994. 
The report evaluates profitability by port region, size (measured by both gross operating
revenue and net investment in plant, property and equipment), type of operation, type of
governmental agency, and extent of planning.  For the purpose of the study, a port has been
defined as being profitable and self-sufficient if it has a net profit before the collection of taxes
and contributions, donations, grants, and subsidies.
<p>
<hr>
<p>
