<html>         
<head>
<title>U.S. MARITIME ADMINISTRATION</title>

<!pn=aa11.htm/page last edited on 1/4/97blh->
</head>

<body>
<center><img src="AA11.gif"></center>
<p>
<center><u>OFFICE OF SHIPYARD REVITALIZATION</u></center>
<p>
<OL>         
         <li type =1><b><u>Mission. </u></b>To promote construction of ships in United States
          shipyards for both foreign and domestic trades, and promote 
          competitiveness of United States shipyards.<p>
         
         <li><b><u>Functions. </u></b>Under the general direction and supervision of the
         Associate Administrator for Shipbuilding and Technology
         Development, the Director, Office of Shipyard Revitalization
         shall:<p>                                                   
        <ol> 
         
        <li type = a>Plan, manage, and report on Maritime Administration funded
         technical studies on shipbuilding performed by contractors
         and other organizations.<p>
         
        <li>Provide technology assessments and make recommendations
         related to shipyards in the United States.<p> 
         
        <li>Identify and stimulate transfer of advanced technologies
         from other fields into the shipbuilding field.<p>
         
        <li>Serve as focal point to bring advanced technical expertise
         to bear on issues of concern to the Maritime Administration
         and the Department of Transportation.<p>

        <li>Represent the Maritime Admiristration, as appropriate, to
         the Government, private sector and academia, including for
         example the Advanced Research Projects Agency.<p>
       </ol>  
</ol>         
<p>
<hr>
<hr>
<p>
