         <html>
         <center><u>OFFICE OF CARGO PREFERENCE</u></center>
<ol>         
         <li type=1><b><u>Mission.</u></b> To formulate national policies and plans and conduct
         programs for the administration and operation of cargo preference 
         activities, and provide liaison with Government shipper
         agencies and others regarding their requirements for guideline
         rates and terms covering U.S. Government and privately-owned
         U.S. flag ships carrying Government-sponsored cargoes.<p>
         
         <li><b><u>Functions.</u></b> Under the general direction and supervision of the
         Associate Administrator for Ship Financial Assistance and Cargo
         Preference, the Director, Office of Cargo Preference shall:<p>
        <ol>         
         <li type=a>Regulate, review, and report on the administration and
         operation of cargo preference activities in accordance with
         section 901(b) of the Merchant Marine Act, 1936, as amended.<p>
         
         <li>Maintain liaison with and advise Government agencies as to
         the availability of U.S.flag shipping, and develop and
         analyze records of U.S.flag participation.<p>
         
         <li>Advise Government shipper agencies and other organizations
         regarding terms covering U.S. Government and privately owned
         U.S. flag ships carrying Government-sponsored cargoes.<p>

         <li>Conduct analyses of discriminatory laws, regulations, and
         practices of foreign governments for use in connection with
         waiver policy on Public Resolution 17.<p>
         
         <li>Process applications for, approve, and administer Export Import 
         Bank waivers.<p>
        </ol>         
</ol> <p>
