         <html>
         <center><u>OFFICE OF COSTS AND RATES</u></center><p>
<ol>         
         <li type=1><b><u>Mission. </u></b>To collect, analyze, and maintain data on the relative
         costs of operating ships under United States and foreign flags,
         determine foreign competition, and compute related rates.<p>
         
         <li><b><u>Functions. </u></b> Under the general direction and supervision of the
         Associate Administrator for Ship Financial Assistance and Cargo
         Preference, the Director, Office of Costs and Rates shall:<p>
        <ol>
         <li type=a>Recommend approval or disapproval of actions related to the
         determination of operating-differential subsidy rates and
         substantiality and extent of foreign flag competition.<p>
         
         <li>Determine eligibility of items of expenses on which subsidy
         is claimed, except maintenance and repair expenses.<p>
         
         <li>Determine amounts of subsidy payments for approved quid pro
         quo costs applicable to final and tentative operating-differential 
         subsidy rates approved by the Maritime Subsidy Board.<p>
         
         <li>Compute rates to determine amounts payable under claims for
         subsidy payment.<p>
         
         <li>Calculate and advise Government shipper agencies and other
         organizations on fair and reasonable guideline rates.<p>
        </ol>
</ol> <p>
<A HREF = "http:aa2.htm">RETURN TO ASSOCIATE ADMINISTRATORS PAGE</A>
