         <center><u>OFFICE OF SEALIFT SUPPORT</u></center>
<ol>         
         <li type=1><b><u>Mission. </u></b>To ensure Maritime Administration provides the
         necessary sealift support to meet its obligations.<p>
         
         <li><b><u>Functions. </u></b>Under the general direction and supervision of the
         Associate Administrator for National Security, the Director,
         Office of Sealift Support shall:<p>
         <ol>
         <li type=a>Develop and ensure compliance with the Maritime Security
         Program, develop the emergency preparedness program for
         sealift support to ensure ship availability, and make
         appropriate recommendations to the U.S. Transportation
         Command, Department of Defense.<p>
         
         <li>Provide liaison with U.S. Transportation Command, the
         National Security Council, and other agencies with sealift
         support activities.<p>
         
         <li>Conduct studies and develop plans for sealift and reserve
         fleet ships including determination of fleet size, etc.,
         required for national security.<p>
         
         <li>Administer the sale and acquisition of vesseis under
         section 510( i ) of the Merchant Marine Act, 1936, as amended,
         Public Law 95-177, and Public Law 10l-595.<p>          

         <li>In coordination with other involved offices, develop and 
         admin1ster the Maritime Administration's program for foreign
         transfer and disposal of vessels, transfer vessels to states
         and other governmental bodies and qualified non-govorment
         parties, conduct competitive bid sales of vessels, report
         all violations of sections 9, 37 (when operative), and 41 of
         the Shipping Act, 1916, as amended, and of conditions of
         agreements, recommend approval or disapproval of applications 
         for banks or trust companies to act as trustees
         pursuant to Public Law 100-710 and 46 CFR Part 221 and
         maintain a roster of approved trustees and mortgagees,
         approve or disapprove release of parties from liabilities
         under existing agreements and guarantees, and prepare and
         sign letters to notify parties of such approval or
         disapproval.<p>
         </ol>
</ol><p>
