</DOCHDR>
         <html>
         <center><u>OFFICE OF SHIP FINANCING</u></center>
         
<ol>         
         <li type=1><b><u>Mission.</u></b> To administer the ship financing guarantee, capital
         construction fund, and construction reserve fund programs of the
         Maritime Administration in accordance with Titles V, VI, and XI
         of the Merchant Marine Act, 1936, as amended.<p>
         
         <li><b><u>Functions.</u></b>Under the general direction and supervision of the
         Associate Administrator for Ship Financial Assistance and Cargo
         Preference, the Director, Office of Ship Financing shall:<p>
        <ol>         
         <li type=a>Recommend approval or disapproval of actions relating to
         award and administration of ship financing guarantee
         contracts, capital construction fund agreements, and
         construction reserve fund agreements.<p>
         
         <li>Direct and coordinate processing of applications for ship
         financing guarantees, capital construction funds, and
         construction reserve funds.<p>
         
         <li>Coordinate and conduct meetings with applicants and 
         approve or disapprove requests for extension of existing escrow
         agreements and interest rates.<p>
         
         <li>Recommend actions where a ship owner's failure to meet
         financial obligations would threaten the interests of the
         United States.<p>
         
         <li>Represent the Maritime Administration on matters relating
         to ship financing guarantees, capital construction funds,
         and construction reserve funds.<p>
        </ol>         
</ol> <p>
