<p>
<h4><center>OFFICE OF THE ASSOCIATE ADMINISTRATOR<br>
SHIP FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE AND CARGO PREFERENCE</CENTER></h4>
<p>

<B>Mission. </B> To formulate, direct, and 
        coordinate operating-
         differential and construction- differential subsidy programs,
         Title XI ship financing guarantees and capital construction
         funds to aid in financing ship construction, reconstruction, and
         reconditioning, marine insurance and marine war risk insurance
         activities, and program financial analysis and approval
         activities.
<P>
         
<B>Functions. </B> Under the general direction and 
         supervision of the
         Maritime Administrator, the Associate Administrator for Ship
         Financial Assistance and Cargo Preference shall provide
         executive direction over the following organizations:
<p>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="AA21.htm"><IMG SRC="AA21.GIF"></A>
<A HREF="AA22.htm"><IMG SRC="AA22.GIF"></A>
<A HREF="AA23.htm"><IMG SRC="AA23.GIF"></A>
<A HREF="AA24.htm"><IMG SRC="AA24.GIF"></A>
<a href="aa25.htm"><img src="aa25.gif"></a>
</center>

<P>
