<body>
<a><center><h4>APPENDIX III: RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM--FY 1995</h4>
</center></a>
<p>
<center><b>Environmental Protection Program Projects</b></center>
<p>
*Cost Shared
<hr>
<p>
<b>Project:</b> Air Emission Reduction Program
<p>
<b>Task:</b><br>
Evaluate a strategy for
diesel engine
particulate emission
reduction.
<p>
<b>Recipient:</b><br>
National Maritime Enhancement Institute at the Massachusetts 
Institute of Technology, Cambridge, MA
<p>
<b>Agreement Number:</b> DTMA91-95-H-00051
<p>
<b>Amount:</b> $69,995
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<b>Project:</b> Air Emission Reduction Program (continued) 
<p>
<b>Task:</b><br>
Joint research with the
U.S. Coast Guard to
provide guidance and
recommendations on
how best to assess
and control air
pollution from marine
engines.
<p>
<b>Recipient:</b><br>
U.S. Coast Guard, Washington, DC
<p>
<b>Agreement Number:</b> MA-5-A45
<p>
<b>Amount:</b> $25,000*
<p>
