<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>U.S. MARITIME ADMINISTRATION</TITLE>

<!pn=och.htm/page edited on 12/7/96blh->
</HEAD>

<BODY>

              <CENTER>OFFICE OF THE CHIEF COUNSEL</CENTER>
<P>
                    
<B>Mission. </B> To provide legal counsel and advice for handling all
         legal matters with which the Maritime Administration is concerned.<P>
         
<B>Functions. </B> Under the general direction and supervision of the
         Maritime Administrator, the Chief Counsel shall:<P>
        <OL>         
         <LI TYPE=a>Serve as the principal legal advisor to the Administrator
         as to legal implications and consequences of actions
         proposed or taken, provide legal representation for the
         Maritime Administration, furnish legal advice and opinions
         to officials at headquarters and the Regions, and approve
         requests for the employment of individuals by non personal
         service contracts to serve as special counsel, witnesses,
         experts, and appraisers as needed for litigation.<P>
         
    <LI> Negotiate and settle or recommend settlement of claims in
         admiralty, just compensation, tort, employee, and claims
         referred for litigation; give legal clearance to applications 
         for Government aid, and provide legal services dealing 
         with acquisition, use and disposal of property, and
         services.  Prepare drafts of proposed legislation, executive 
         orders, and legislative reports to congressional
         committees, the Office of Management and Budget, and other
         Federal agencies.<P>
         
    <LI>Assist the Justice Department in the trial, appeal, and
         settlement of litigation, and represent the administration
         before Federal, state, and local courts and before
         administrative agencies of the Government with the
         permission of the Department of Justice.<P>

     <LI>Review format and legality of external regulations, notices,
         and other documents of the Maritime Administraticn and Maritime 
         Subsidy Board, and coordinate their preparation and
         publication in the Federal Register.<P>
         
     <LI>Prepare and approve as to form and legality contracts,
         agreements, deeds, leases, performance bonds, and related
         documents, and approve citizenship status of applicants
         under the governing statutes.<P>
         
     <LI>Serve as a member of the Maritime Subsidy Board and
         designate an individual to serve as Maritime Administration's 
         Freedom of Information and Privacy Acts Officer.<P>
     </OL>         
<P>
<HR>
<p>
THE OFFICE OF CHIEF COUNSEL IS SUPPORTED BY THE FOLLOWING DIVISIONS
</H5></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="OCH1.TXT"><IMG SRC="OCH1.GIF"></A>
<A HREF="OCH2.TXT"><IMG SRC="OCH2.GIF"></A>
<A HREF="OCH3.TXT"><IMG SRC="OCH3.GIF"></A>
<A HREF="OCH4.TXT"><IMG SRC="OCH4.GIF"></A>
<A HREF="OCH5.TXT"><IMG SRC="OCH5.GIF"></A>
<A HREF="OCH6.TXT"><IMG SRC="OCH6.GIF"></A></CENTER>
<P>
<hr>
<hr>
<p>
</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
