<html>
<head>
<title>U.S. MARITIME ADMINISTRATION</TITLE>

<!pn=aa62.htm/page last edited on 12/6/96blh->
</head>
<body>

<center><u>OFFICE OF INFORMATION RESOURCES MANAGEMENT</u></center>
<p>
<center><img align=TOP BORDER=4 SRC="bill44.jpg"></center>
<p>
<hr>
<b>Mission. </b>
To plan, design, develop, program, document, and
maintain the administration's computer-based information
systems.<p>
         
<b>Functions. </b>
Under the general direction and supervision of the
Associate Administrator for Administration, the Director, Office
of Information Resources Management shall:<p>
<ol>
<li type=a>Evaluate existing and proposed information resources management 
systems, excluding records, forms, reports, voice and facsimile 
telecommunications management; determine cost and benefits of acquiring 
new information technology equipment and systems, monitor and coordinate 
information technology contracts for developmental or operating information 
technology systems and contractual data entry services; and develop and 
monitor long and short range information technology plans.<p>
         
<li>Provide systems software support, and select, test, implement, 
maintain, and modify system software modules.<p>
         
<li>Analyze, design, develop, program, document, install, and
maintain computer-based information systems, select data
bases, and effective internal information technology systems.<p>
         
<li>Develop and implement procedures for the flow of information
between Maritime Administration users and the Department of Transportation
on computer-related issues, and support the administration's computer
communications interfaces and peripheral devices.<p>

<li>Develop and implement quality control and assurance
measures, and implement safeguards to ensure compliance
with applicable laws and regulations.<p>
</ol>
<p>     
<HR>
