<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA: Who We Are</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#99bbff">
<H1><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Who We Are</FONT></H1>
<P><A HREF="hist.htm">Vermont-NEA was founded in 1850</A> as the Vermont
Teachers' Association. Vermont-NEA now is a state-level affiliate of the
<A HREF="http://www.nea.org">National Education Association</A>, the largest
professional association in the United States, with 2.2 million members.</P>
<P>Educators in communities throughout Vermont are organized as
<A HREF="vtnea02.htm">local affiliates</A> of Vermont-NEA.  Educators also join
<A HREF="vtnea03.htm">subject area affiliates</A> of Vermont-NEA, organizations
dedicated to particular professional specialties.</P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea26.htm">Vermont-NEA positions</A> are determined
democratically through an annual Representative Assembly.  Vermont-NEA policy is
directed by
<A HREF="vtnea04.htm">officers and board members</A> selected in statewide
elections.  Vermont-NEA's program is implemented by 
<A HREF="vtnea28.htm">volunteer committees of Association members</A> and a
<A HREF="vtnea27.htm">full time staff</A>.</P>
