<TITLE>Vermont-NEA Opportunities for Educators</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#99bbff">
<H1><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Opportunities for Educators</FONT></H1>
<P><A HREF="honor.htm"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> 
Congratulations to Peggy Dorta of Underhill Central School -- she is
<A HREF="honor.htm">Vermont's 1997 Teacher of the Year</A>. </P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea06.htm"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> 
Vermont-NEA members share their <A HREF="vtnea06.htm">Best Lessons and Units</A>.</P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea07.htm"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>  These
<A HREF="vtnea07.htm">Tips and Ideas</A> are intended for teachers who are just
beginning their careers.</P>
<P><A HREF="scholar.htm"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>  The sons
and daughters of Vermont-NEA members are eligible for the <A HREF="scholar.htm">Vermont-NEA/Maida
F. Townsend Scholarship</A>.</P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea09.htm"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> 
Vermont-NEA will offer an impressive program of professional  workshops and
exhibits at  the October 22 - 24, 1997 <A HREF="vtnea09.htm">Educators'
Convention</A>.</P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea10.htm"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>  Educators
explore and debate education issues in this <A HREF="vtnea10.htm">Professional
Exchange</A>.</P>
<P><A HREF="green.htm"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>  Vermont-NEA
sponsors the annual <A HREF="green.htm">Vermont Green Up Poster Contest</A> and
offers an incentive for the classroom of the teacher (must be a Vermont-NEA
member!) of the student who wins.</P>
<P><A HREF="sw.htm"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>  Read and
comment on the most recent draft of Vermont-NEA's <B><I><A HREF="sw-3.htm">Schools
That Work</A></I></B> report.</P>
<P><A HREF="links-2.htm"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>  These
websites of particular interest to educators are recommended by Vermont-NEA
members and hot linked for your convenience. <A HREF="links-2.htm">Come
explore!</A></P>
