<TITLE>Vermont-NEA Committees</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#99bbff">
<H1><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Vermont-NEA Committees</FONT></H1>
<P><B><I>These committees are appointed by the Vermont-NEA President. They
are comprised of Association members who volunteer their time and service.</I></B></P>
<H2><B>Teaching  &amp; Learning Steering Committee
</B></H2>
<P><B>Chair:</B> Vermont-NEA President Angelo Dorta</P>
<P><B>Comittee Members:</B> Chairs of each  Activity Committee, plus other
at-large members appointed by the President
</P>
<P><B>Function:</B> Advise the President and Board on T &amp; L policy and
program areas. Oversee and coordinate the work of the Activity Committees. 
</P>
<H2>Convention Planning</H2>
<P><B>Committee Members:</B> Joan Alexander, Orleans (co-chair); Stephanie
Keitel, Montpelier; Judy Allard, Burlington (co-chair); Lucinda Clark, Proctor;
Stephanie O'Leary, Essex Junction
</P>
<P><B>Vermont-NEA Staff:</B> Laurie B. Huse
</P>
<P><B>Function:</B> Set the Convention theme and screen workshops. Oversee the
Convention. 
</P>
<H2>Sponsorships/Partnerships
</H2>
<P><B>Committee Members:</B> Mike Jennings, Northfield (chair); Bill Haines,
Montpelier; Kevin Mack, Rutland; Dot Reeve, Morristown; Anne Stevens, Craftsbury
</P>
<P><B>Vermont-NEA Staff: </B>Laurie B. Huse
</P>
<P><B>Function:</B> Screen requests for sponsorship and / or partnership with
Vermont-NEA. Oversee relationships with partners and sponsored activities, such
as Scholars Bowl and Vermont Green-up. 
</P>
<H2>Publishing
</H2>
<P><B>Committee Members:</B> Stephanie Keitel, Montpelier (chair); Chris
Varney, Hinesburg; Janet Van Fleet, Montpelier; David Schoales, Morrisville;
Carol Hinchey, Essex Junction
</P>
<P><B>Vermont-NEA Staff:</B> Laurie B. Huse
</P>
<P><B>Function:</B> Solicit, recognize, and publicize the best professional
work of Vermont-NEA members.
</P>
<H2>In-Service
</H2>
<P><B>Committee Members:</B> Delia Clark, Essex Town; David Ely, Chittenden
South; David Schoales, Morrisville; Sandra Stanley, Northeast Kingdom; Marilyn
Gillis, Milton; Greg Smist, Springfield; Sharon Baack, Barre
</P>
<P><B>Vermont-NEA Staff:</B> Ellen David Friedman</P>
<P><B>Function:</B> Survey the successful models of staff-designed and
staff-led professional development programs in Vermont schools. Identify key
levers to gain effective direction of professional development activities,
including through collective bargaining and collaboration on relevant policy
with school board and school administration. 
</P>
<H2>Conferences
</H2>
<P><B>Committee Members:</B> Donna Cote, Burlington; Lisa Champagne, Windsor;
Tom Luce, Flood Brook
</P>
<P><B>Vermont-NEA Staff:</B> Ellen David Friedman
</P>
<P><B>Function:</B> Set program area goals. Design conference schedule.
Oversee conferences.  
</P>
