<HR>
<H2><A HREF="mailto:best@vtnea.org"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>
  Call for abstracts...  Submit your best lessons and units
</H2>
<P>The Vermont-NEA Publishing Committee invites Association members to submit
descriptions of their very best, most popular and effective classroom lessons
and units. The committee will review the descriptions and pick the best for
sharing and publicizing throughout the state, including here on the Vermont-NEA
Home Page.
</P>
<P>Send your best ideas to the Vermont-NEA Publishing Committee. Please include
such back up material as kids' work, lesson plans, or work sheets with your
abstract. Also, be sure to answer these 7 questions as part of your submission:
	</P>
<OL>
<LI>What is the title of your &quot;BEST&quot;  lesson or unit?</LI>
<LI>What is the subject area(s)?</LI>
<LI>What is the students' grade level?	</LI>
<LI>Describe what you did, what activity(s) the lesson or unit includes. 	</LI>
<LI>What resources did you use?  	</LI>
<LI>What is your method of assessment? 	</LI>
<LI>Your name, school, e-mail address, and phone number -- in case a fellow
educator wants more information.
</LI></OL>
<P> E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:best@vtnea.org">best@vtnea.org</A> or snail mail:
Vermont-NEA, 10 Wheelock Street, Montpelier, VT 05602-3737.</P>
