<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA Scholarship</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<H1><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Scholarships available to sons and daughters of
Vermont-NEA members
</FONT></H1>
<P><I><B>Scholarship applicants will describe how they would revitalize
community interest in public education</B></I></P>
<P>The sons and daughters of Vermont-NEA members -- twelfth graders,
undergraduates, and graduate students -- are eligible to apply for
Vermont-NEA/Maida F. Townsend scholarships. The $1000 scholarships, established
in 1991, are awarded annually at the Vermont-NEA Representative Assembly. 
</P>
<P>The scholarship awards are based on merit, not financial need. Students
majoring in any discipline are eligible to apply, but preference may be given to
those majoring in education, or having that intention. Awards are made directly
to the students, not to their colleges. Students may reapply for the award, but
may receive an award only once.
</P>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">How to Apply</FONT>
</H2>
<P>The scholarship application requires the submission of transcripts and two
letters of recommendation. Twelfth graders must have one recommendation from a
counselor/administrator, and one from a classroom teacher. College students 
must have one recommendation from a professor in his/her major area and one from
a professor who can be outside of the major area. 
</P>
<P>Each applicant must submit an essay with a maximum of 400 words. The theme
is decided by the scholarship committee on an annual basis. The 1997 theme is: 
<B>&quot;How I would revitalize community interest in public education.&quot;
</B>
</P>
<P>The scholarship application cover letter must include the student's
educational and professional plans, as well as a brief statement which
highlights those qualities which make the applicant unique. Along with the other
materials, applicants should submit a listing of extra curricular and community
activities.
</P>
<P>An official Cover Sheet must be filled out and must accompany all
scholarship application material. Contact Vermont-NEA for a copy of the Cover
Sheet. Phone: 1-800-649-6375   E-mail: scholar@vtnea.org
</P>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">The Judges</FONT>
</H2>
<P>The scholarship fund is governed by a board of trustees, which is the same
as the entire Vermont-NEA Board of Directors. The Vermont-NEA president appoints
two board members and an at-large-member to the committee annually. A
chairperson is appointed for a two year term.  These are the members of the 1997
Scholarship Committee: Judy Allard, chair; Cherrie Torrey; and Barbara O'Neil,
member-at-large.
</P>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Deadline
</FONT></H2>
<P>Applications with an official Cover Sheet must be received at Vermont-NEA
Headquarters by the end of the business day on February 14, 1997. The address: 
Vermont-NEA, 10 Wheelock, Street Montpelier, Vermont 05602-3737</P>
