<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA Educators' Convention</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0DCC0">
<H1><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">Vermont-NEA Educators' Convention</FONT></H1>
<P>The Vermont-NEA Educators' Convention is held on Wednesday evening,
Thursday, and Friday of the third full week of each October. In 1997, the 146th
annual Vermont-NEA Educators' Convention is scheduled for October 22-23-24. 
</P>
<P> The Convention will open with an education exhibition at the South
Burlington Sheraton Conference Center, starting at 5:00 p.m. and closing at 8:00
p.m. on Wednesday evening, October 22. The exhibition will continue from 8:00
a.m. till 2:00 p.m. on Thursday, October 23. </P>
<P>A selection of professional workshops will be offered throughout the day on
Thursday, along with a series of Vermont-NEA Scholars' Bowl matches featuring
top students from Vermont high schools.
</P>
<P>The Convention General Assembly -- keynote address and entertainment -- will
convene at 10:30 a.m. on Thursday. </P>
<P>On Friday, October 24, Vermont-NEA Professional Affiliates will hold their
meetings throughout the state.</P>
<HR>
<P>Persons interested in presenting workshops at the Vermont-NEA Convention
should send an application request to Vermont-NEA, 10 Wheelock Street,
Montpelier, VT 05602.</P>
<P>Vermont-NEA's official <I>Convention Workshop Application Form</I> will be
available by February 1 and will be mailed to all who have submitted a request.
Applications will be accepted till April 15, 1997. The decision about which
workshops to accept will be made in early May.</P>
<HR>
<P>Persons interested in purchasing exhibit space at the Vermont-NEA Convention
should contact the Education Sales Association of New England (ESANE), P.O. Box
538, Foxboro, MA 02035. Phone: (508) 543-7778</P>
