<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA Green Up</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#80FF00">
<H1><FONT COLOR="#004000">Green Up Vermont Poster Contest </FONT></H1>
<P>Green Up Day, the first Saturday in May, is a <A HREF="green-3.htm">Vermont
tradition</A>.  It is the day set aside each spring for volunteers across the
state to pick up winter's refuse and &quot;Green Up&quot; our beautiful Vermont.
Part of the Green Up tradition is the annual student poster contest. This year's
winning design will be reproduced in full color, distributed statewide, and used
to promote Green Up 1997. <A HREF="green-1.htm">A third grader won</A> the
contest in 1995, and
<A HREF="green-2.htm">a seventh grader won</A> in 1996. The 1997 winner will be
announced at an awards banquet in Montpelier on April 18.</P>
<P>Vermont-NEA has established a Partnership with Green Up Vermont and is proud
to sponsor the Green Up Poster Contest. We provide advertising and a $200 award
(to be used in the classroom!) to the Vermont-NEA member whose student wins the
contest. Also, Vermont-NEA members constitute half the panel of poster contest
judges. </P>
<P>All Vermont students, grades K-12, are eligible to submit one poster design
for judging. A single overall winning design is selected, but posters first are
judged and a winner selected for each county and statewide for each of these
grade-level categories:  K-4, 5-8 and 9-12.  
</P>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#004000">Contest Rules</FONT> </H2>
<OL>
<LI>Any Vermont K-12 student may submit one design.</LI>
<LI>All posters must be in a vertical format, 11 X 14 inches. Any other size or
format will disqualify the poster.</LI>
<LI>This information must be included on an <B><I>Official Entry Form</I></B>
attached to the back of the poster:
<UL>
<LI>Student's full name, address and grade</LI>
<LI> Parent/guardian's full name, daytime phone and evening phone</LI>
<LI>School name, address, county and phone</LI>
<LI>Teacher's full name</LI>
<LI>Click here <A HREF="form.htm"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> 
or call Vermont-NEA (1-800-649-6375) for an <B><I>Official Entry Form</I></B>,
or make your own. <B><I>Missing information will disqualify the poster.</I></B></LI></UL></LI>
<LI>Entries must be delivered by January 31 each year to: Green Up Vermont,
P.O. Box 1191, Montpelier, Vermont 05601-1191</LI></OL>
<H2> <FONT COLOR="#004000">Winning Rules &amp; Advice</FONT> </H2>
<OL>
<LI>The poster must relate to litter clean up.</LI>
<LI>The poster must include the words GREEN UP.</LI>
<LI>	The poster art must depict or relate to VERMONT.</LI>
<LI>Computer art is not permitted.</LI>
<LI>An <B><I>Official Entry Form</I></B> MUST be attached to the back of
every poster.</LI>
<LI>Remember that judging is based on:
<UL>
<LI>Originality</LI>
<LI>Visual Simplicity</LI>
<LI>Clarity of Message</LI>
<LI>Visual Impact from a Distance (Avoid tiny detail!)</LI></UL></LI></OL>
<H2 ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT COLOR="#004000">Scholarship Awards</FONT></H2>
<MENU>
<LI>Overall Winner: $250</LI>
<LI> K-4, 5-8 and 9-12 Winners: $75 each</LI></MENU>
<H2 ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT COLOR="#004000">Teacher Incentive</FONT> </H2>
<P>The Vermont-NEA Partnership/Sponsorship Committee will award $200 to the
teacher whose student wins the Green Up Vermont Poster Contest. Only Vermont-NEA
members are eligible. The money is for the winning teacher's use in his/her
classroom. 
</P>
<P><FONT SIZE="-2">All rights for the use and reproduction of posters will
belong to Green Up Vermont, Inc. Posters will not be returned after judging.
Questions should be directed to: Green Up Vermont, P.O. Box 1191, Montpelier, VT
05601-1191   Phone: (802) 229-4586</FONT></P>
