<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA Hot Links for Educators</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<H1><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Websites Recommended for Educators</FONT></H1>
<P><B><I>These websites are recommended by educators, for educators. Just
click the apples to start exploring. And <A HREF="mailto:links@vtnea.org">let
us know</A> if there's a site you think should be added to this list.</I></B></P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.cit.state.vt.us:80/vhs/"><IMG
SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> <B>Vermont Historical Society</B>  This
site includes information about Vermont history, historical sites, collections,
projects and research.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.cit.state.vt.us/educ/"><IMG
SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> <B>Vermont State Department of Education</B>
 Information about education in Vermont is featured on this site, along with
links to Vermont schools.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://crs.uvm.edu/schlrpt"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>
<B>Vermont Department of Education School Reports</B>  The Department of
Education School Reports are provided for individual schools. The indicators
include general information, staff resources, risk factors, financial resources,
financial expenditures, and student performance information. Data are reported
over multiple years, and current year statewide data are reported when
available. </P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.floodbrook.k12.vt.us/veeone/starter.html"><IMG
SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>  <B>VeeOne Information Resources</B>  IBM
Reinventing Schools Partnership and the Vermont State Department of Education
collaborated to build this site. It is designed to provide information resources
for Vermont educators.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.nea.org/cet/links"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>
 <B>NEA Education Links (EDLinks)</B>  This area on the National Education
Association's website is reserved as a showcase for the best World Wide Web
links about Teaching, Learning and Technology.  Each link in the NEA database is
there because education practitioners, parents and kids who visit NEA's site
have asked that it be included.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><A HREF="http://www.edweek.org/qc/states/vt-rc.htm"><IMG
SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> <B>Quality Counts</B> is an <I>Education
Week</I> report that takes a look at learning in the United States. The report
includes state-by-state report cards and a lengthy summary of each state's
educational progress and problems. Our state ranks among the best in the nation,
with grades that place Vermont third among the top twelve states. </P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.gene.com/ae"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>
 <B>Access Excellence</B> This site is a national educational program sponsored
by the biotechnology industry pioneer, Genentech, Inc., that puts high school
biology teachers in touch with their colleagues, scientists and critical sources
of new scientific information through an online network. It's a virtual beehive
of activity! </P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.education-world.com/"><IMG
SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> <B>Education-World</B>  This site is a
huge educational resource that includes: links to schools throughout the state,
nation and world; education news; site reviews; expert opinions; and an
education site database with over 20,000 URLs.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://www.pitsco.com/p/ask.html"><IMG
SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> <B>Ask An Expert</B>  Teachers or
students can send e-mail from this site to an expert and receive a timely
response. Extensive listings cover all curriculum areas.</P>
<P><A HREF="http://ericir.syr.edu/"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>
<B>askERIC</B>  Educators can access Lesson Plans from the Virtual Library on
this all inclusive site or search the ERIC documents database.</P>
<HR>
