<TITLE>Vermont-NEA Child Development Calendar</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<H1><FONT COLOR="#008000">A Child's Development Calendar</FONT></H1><IMG
SRC="devcal10.jpg" ALIGN="right" WIDTH="400" HEIGHT="591">
<P><B><I><FONT SIZE="+1">Children grow and learn in their own special way
and time. These pages are filled with games, book titles, and ideas to help you
share in your child's playing and learning. At the top of the pages is a
suggested age range for the activities. This is a guide, not a rule. Do any or
all of the activities that seem fun for you and your child.</FONT></I></B></P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea16.htm">The Observer:</A> Your new baby, birth to 6 months</P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea17.htm">The Toucher:</A> Your baby, 6 - 12 months</P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea18.htm">The Mover:</A> Your pre-toddler, 10 - 20 months</P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea19.htm">The Builder:</A> Your toddler, 17 - 26 months</P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea20.htm">The Super Helper:</A> Your mature toddler, 23 - 32
months</P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea21.htm">The Butterfly:</A> Your talker, 28 - 38 months</P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea22.htm">The Questioner:</A> Your child, 35 - 46 months</P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea23.htm">The Expert:</A> Your young preschooler, 44 - 50
months</P>
<P><A HREF="vtnea29.htm">The Preschooler:</A> Your child, 48 - 62 months</P>
<HR>
<P><I>The paper version of this child development calendar has been published
and distributed to schools and hospitals (for new moms) throughout the state by
the Vermont-National Education Association. A limited number of
<A HREF="mailto:devcal@vtnea.org">copies are still available</A>.</I></P>
<P><I>Stephanie Keitel of the Vermont Speech, Language and Hearing Association
wrote the calendar. Sharon Damkot of the Vermont Educational Media Association
compiled the book lists. Artist and Vermont-NEA member Steve Barrows drew the
illustrations. Vermont-NEA Communications Director Laurie Huse edited the
project.</I></P>
