<TITLE>Vermont-NEA History-1</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<TABLE BORDER="0" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TR>
<TD>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">Carolyn S. Woodruff</FONT></H2><B>In 1914, Carolyn
S. Woodruff became the first woman to serve as president of the Vermont
Teachers' Association. She later served as president of the National Education
Association.</B>
</TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="file:///c|/vtnea/woodruff.jpg" WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="439"></TD></TR></TABLE>
