<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA Best Lessons</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1>Seventh Grade Geography Project Ecosystems
</H1>
<H4>Submitted by Barbara Barbour, Windsor</H4>
<P>My seventh grade geography classes are given coordinates of an imaginary
island. Students, in groups of three or four, locate the island and describe the
inhabitants, climate and vegetation. They are instructed to develop communities
on the island. Students are to write about what the environment consists of in
order to sustain the inhabitants, as well as the effect each inhabitant has on
the island's environment. </P>
<P>Students study climate, food chains, biomes, adaptation, economy,
government, industry and the effects of each. Simcity is used as one of the
learning tools. Students learn research, outlining, writing, and presentation
skills in their English classes and use these skills to write an essay about
their island and present that information to the class. Instruction in social
studies and science classes support the project, as well.
</P>
<P>Call Barbara Barbour for more information: 802-436-2038. 
</P>
