<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA Best Lessons</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<H1>Ocean Study/Water Unit
</H1>
<H4>Submitted by Harriet Grenier, Elizabeth Sabens, Mary Mello, Olivia
Salzberg, Lisa Kitchen, Terry Hodgdon, and Ellen Gittelsohn, Montpelier</H4>
<P>A group of teachers at Union Elementary School in Montpelier collaborated on
a thematic unit about water and ocean. </P>
<P>We built constructions from tubing and rain spouts to observe and experiment
with water flow and force. We constructed inflatable structures out of clear
plastic for creating an underwater habitat and a simulated submarine. 
</P>
<P>The projects encompass each field of study: science, math, language arts,
history, music, art and health. There are literature based activities on the
ocean in the following categories: seashore, tides and reefs; the ocean floor;
plants and animals; folklore and myths; ships and pirates; and ecology and
pollution issues. We also created a musical show entitled &quot;Raindrop
Journey,&quot; which showcases the children's knowledge learned from this unit.
</P>
<P>If you are interested in these materials or ideas, contact: Harriet Grenier,
Elizabeth Sabens, Mary Mello, Olivia Salzberg, Lisa Kitchen, Terry Hodgdon, or
Ellen Gittelsohn at Union Elementary, 1 Park Avenue, Montpelier, VT 05602.
Phone: 802-223-6343.</P>
