<BODY BGCOLOR="#A4C8F0">
<H1><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">10 documents to keep in your professional records
file and portfolio </FONT></H1>
<P><B>1.</B>	Your teaching license and Individual Professional Development
Plan (IPDP) 
</P>
<P><B>2.</B>	Transcripts of degrees and college credits, including attendance 
</P>
<P><B>3.</B>	Letters of hire, an individual employee contract, if you signed
one, supplemental contracts for extra duty, teaching schedules   </P>
<P><B>4.</B>	Your local Association's Master Contract  </P>
<P><B>5.</B>	Salary and payroll records,  records pertinent to your
retirement, records of leave accrual and use  </P>
<P><B>6.	</B>Evaluations, growth plans, commendations, awards, and honors 
</P>
<P><B>7.</B>	Records of incidents involving discipline 
</P>
<P><B>8.</B>	Records of referrals of students with special needs  </P>
<P><B>9.</B>	Copies of all correspondence from administrators or the district 
</P>
<P><B>10.</B>	Proof of Association membership, the National Education
Association's $l million liability insurance policy  brochure </P>
