<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA Professional Exchange</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<H1><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">At no time have I been prouder</FONT></H1>
<P><B>By Richard Roy, Teacher, South Burlington High School</B>
</P>
<P>I have been teaching for 26 years and have been a member of Vermont-NEA
since 1974.  At no time have I been prouder to be a member of the Association
than in November when I read an earlier draft of Schools That Work.  For too
long have we appeared to be reacting to the criticism that inundates those of us
who have given our lives to this profession.  For too long have we failed to
speak strongly about what our experience and knowledge tell us are the problems
facing schools.  And for too long have we failed to state strongly what are our
recommendations for dealing with the problems we face.  
</P>
<P>I particularly applaud the recommendations that deal with student decorum,
the emphasis on content over process and self-esteem, and the academic training
of prospective teachers.  
</P>
<P>I look forward to the Association's assuming a strong position in any
discussion about the future of education in Vermont. </P>
<HR>
