<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA Schools That Work Letter</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<P ALIGN="CENTER"><A HREF="sw-3.htm"><I>Schools That Work</I> Contents</A> |
<A HREF="index.htm">Home</A></P>
<H1><FONT COLOR="#800000">A message to Association members from Vermont-NEA
President Angelo J. Dorta</FONT></H1>
<P>As your representative organization, Vermont-NEA is keenly aware of the
monumental obstacles which you and your colleagues must overcome every day as
you strive to make Vermont schools work. We hear about the discipline problems,
the erosion of support for your high academic standards, the increasing demands
on your time for non-instructional tasks, and on top of it all, the constant
barrage of negative publicity about education and teachers.  	</P>
<P>We know that Vermont-NEA members want to be in the forefront of the debate
regarding change in our schools. You have told us that you do not want to be in
the position of simply reacting to each and every quick fix that politicians or
others dream up. You have told us that you want to shape the discussion, that
you want to be heard and respected. You have told us that you are tired of
assuming responsibility for the social problems we face as a community, state
and nation.  	</P>
<P>Now, Vermont-NEA has drafted a report, called <I><A HREF="sw.htm">Schools
That Work</A></I>, that speaks to educators' expectations of our schools,
administrators, parents and communities. The report includes the messages we
hear consistently from Association members throughout the state.  
</P>
<P>Every Vermont-NEA member must have an opportunity to help shape what could
be a very important document. To that end:</P>
<OL>
<LI>	The draft document was mailed to every local elected leader in the state.</LI>
<LI>The draft document was revised by the Vermont-NEA Board on December 7,
1996, and  was reprinted in the January 1997 issue of <I>Vermont-NEA Today</I>,
mailed to every Association member. </LI>
<LI>The Vermont-NEA Board approved more changes at their January meeting.</LI>
<LI>Any member may call 1-800-649-6375 for copies of <I>Schools That Work</I>.</LI>
<LI>Any group of Association members may add their collective wisdom to the
document by compiling and submitting their views.</LI>
<LI>Members of the Vermont-NEA Board of Directors or the Vermont-NEA staff have
been available to help facilitate a discussion about <I>Schools That Work</I>.
</LI>
<LI>	Members submitted their views about the document to me at Vermont-NEA
through January.</LI>
<LI>	Finally, a meeting was held on Saturday, January 25, at the Capitol Plaza
in Montpelier to discuss the revised version of <I>Schools That Work</I>. </LI></OL>
<HR>
<P ALIGN="CENTER"><A HREF="sw-3.htm"><I>Schools That Work</I> Contents</A> |
