<HEAD>
<TITLE></TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<P ALIGN="CENTER"><A HREF="sw.htm"><I>Schools That Work</I> Contents</A> |
<A HREF="vtnea200.htm">Opportunities for Educators</A> | <A HREF="index.htm">Home</A></P>
<H1><FONT COLOR="#800000">Why read <I>Schools That Work?</I></FONT> </H1>
<P><I><A HREF="sw.htm">Schools That Work</A></I> is a report on education
that is unique, because it is based on the opinions of educators. Here are a few
of the recommendations in the report which may be controversial: </P>
<OL>
<LI><A HREF="sw-4.htm">Require greater decorum in schools, including stricter
standards for attendance, dress, language, behavior and discipline.</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="sw-4.htm">Work to remove disruptive students from school.</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="sw-4.htm">Oppose scheduling of non-academic activities that take
students out of class.</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="sw-6.htm">Make greater academic rigor a chief goal.</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="sw-5.htm">Require entering teachers to pass the National Teacher
Examination and serve a two-year probation.</A> </LI>
<LI><A HREF="sw-5.htm">Advocate more rigorous evaluation of teachers.</A>
</LI>
<LI><A HREF="sw-5.htm">Require that all teachers achieve a master's degree or
equivalent number of credits within seven years of receiving a permanent
license.</A></LI></OL>
<HR>
