<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA History-10</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<TABLE BORDER="0" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TR>
<TD>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">J. Newton Perrin</FONT></H2><B>J. Newton Perrin,
superintendent of the Orange-Washington School District, served  as president of
the Vermont Education Association in 1956. In remarks opening the October 4-5,
1956 VEA Convention, he said: &quot;Through participation in this convention, we
hope all will be stimulated to improve instruction and to strengthen our
organized teaching profession.&quot;</B>
</TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="perrin.jpg" WIDTH="200" HEIGHT="261"></TD></TR></TABLE>
