<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA History-8</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<TABLE BORDER="0" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TR>
<TD>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">Ruth A. Spooner</FONT></H2><B>Ruth Spooner of
Burlington served  as president of the Vermont Education Association in 1967. In
remarks opening the 1967 VEA Convention, she said: &quot;We know that the
curricula many of us live with from day to day are not meeting the needs of the
youngsters. As teachers, we must become involved in curriculum revision.&quot;</B>
</TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="spooner.jpg" WIDTH="200" HEIGHT="240"></TD></TR></TABLE>
