<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA History-9</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<TABLE BORDER="0" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TR>
<TD>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">May L. Willard</FONT></H2><B>May Willard of Derby
served  as president of the Vermont Education Association in 1968. In remarks
opening the October 10-11, 1968 VEA Convention, she said: &quot;Teachers must
explore... new ideas and adopt those which facilitate both teaching and
learning. We must, however, remember that there is still a place for many of the
older techniques that have stood the test of time.&quot;</B>  
</TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="willard.jpg" WIDTH="200" HEIGHT="285"></TD></TR></TABLE>
