<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA History-11</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<TABLE BORDER="0" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TR>
<TD>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">Eric  P.  Scott</FONT></H2><B>Eric Scott, drafting
teacher and chair of the Industrial and Fine Arts Department at Brattleboro
Union High School, served Vermont-NEA as president in 1972-73 and as Vermont's
representative on the National Education Association Board of Directors. In the
photo, taken in November 1976, he is receiving an NEA Distinguished Service
Award from Alice Perine for his meritorious service on the NEA Representative
Assembly Planning Committee.</B></TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="scott.jpg" WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="245"></TD></TR></TABLE>
