<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA History-13</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<TABLE BORDER="0" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TR>
<TD>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">Lawrence L. Coffin</FONT></H2><B>Larry Coffin, a
teacher at Oxbow Union High School, served Vermont-NEA  as President in 1975-76.
&quot;...most educational progress is achieved by local school personnel working
directly with children,&quot; he said in his welcome to the 1975 VEA Convention.
He continued: &quot;Despite the fact that  teachers often underwrite the cost of
research and technique development with their own time and money, there seems to
be no lack of willingness on their part to be involved. Those groups that fail
to recognize the role of the teacher in the development of new materials and
processes doom their projects to failure.&quot;</B>
</TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="coffin.jpg" WIDTH="200" HEIGHT="293"></TD></TR></TABLE>
