<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA History-12</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<TABLE BORDER="0" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TR>
<TD>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">Alice N. Perine</FONT></H2><B>Alice Perine, a
teacher at Middlebury Union High School, served Vermont-NEA  as president in
1976-77. &quot;VEA stands for Advocacy, and Advocacy and Professionalism are one
and the same,&quot; she wrote in a 1977 editorial. She continued: &quot;Does it
dignify the profession to accept less than needed to get the job done right or
to receive too little income to live decently?&quot;</B>
</TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="perine.jpg" WIDTH="200" HEIGHT="315"></TD></TR></TABLE>
