<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA History-14</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<TABLE BORDER="0" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TR>
<TD>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">James Kiehle</FONT></H2><B>Jim Kiehle, a social
studies teacher at Brattleboro Union High School, served Vermont-NEA as
President in 1977-78. Jim first proposed changing the name of the Association
from Vermont Education Association to Vermont-National Education Association.
His proposal was approved at the Corporation meeting at the 1982 VEA
Representative Assembly. This photo was taken at the start of his term in 1977,
before  winter set in.</B>
</TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="kiehle.jpg" WIDTH="200" HEIGHT="287"></TD></TR></TABLE>
