<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA History-3</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<TABLE BORDER="0" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TR>
<TD>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">Ronald G. Williams</FONT></H2><B>Ron Williams, a
teacher at St. Albans Town School,  served in 1978-79 as Vermont-NEA's
first-ever full-time, paid president. After leaving office, he attended Vermont
Law School and worked as an attorney in Rutland. He was killed in a motorcycle
accident in 1989. A sign on his desk read: &quot;It's too bad that the people
who really know how to run the country are busy TEACHING SCHOOL.&quot;</B>
</TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="williams.jpg" WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="488"></TD></TR></TABLE>
