<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA History-15</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<TABLE BORDER="0" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TR>
<TD>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">David Bongiolatti</FONT></H2><B>David Bongiolatti,
a 7th grade history teacher at Barre Town School, served Vermont-NEA as
President in 1979-81. After leaving Vermont-NEA, David became Executive Director
of the Mississippi Association of Educators and then the Texas State Teachers
Association. &quot;We owe it to our profession to demand decent salaries for
ourselves,&quot; he told the members of the Orange Southwest Education
Association in October, 1980. He continued: &quot;Children and Education are not
well served by underfunded schools and underpaid teachers.&quot;</B>
</TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="bongo.jpg" WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="214"></TD></TR></TABLE>
