<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA History-4</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<TABLE BORDER="0" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TR>
<TD>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">Maida F. Townsend</FONT></H2>
<B>Maida Townsend, a French teacher from Vergennes Union High School, served as
Vermont-NEA President for an unprecedented eight years, from 1981 till 1989. 
She led the Association in its successful effort to raise teachers' salaries &quot;up
from 51st&quot; in the national rankings. Since leaving office, Maida has taught
French and Spanish at Winooski High School.</B>
</TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="townsend.jpg" WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="200"></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P ALIGN="CENTER"><A HREF="hist.htm">Vermont-NEA History</A> |
