<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA History-5</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0">
<TABLE BORDER="0" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<TR>
<TD>
<H2><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">Marlene R. Burke</FONT></H2><B>Marlene &quot;Molly&quot;
Burke, a history teacher at Rutland High school, served Vermont-NEA as president
from 1989 till 1995. She conceived the Maida F. Townsend Scholarship and guided
the Association through the successful battle against the proposal to establish
a statewide teachers' contract. (The contract would have sacrificed hard won
local Association contracts and many teacher rights and protections.) After
leaving office, Molly returned to teaching history at Rutland's new high school.
</B>
</TD>
<TD><IMG SRC="mburke.jpg" WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="426"></TD></TR></TABLE>
