<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vermont-NEA Home Page</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="99bbff">
<P ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT COLOR="#FF0000"><A HREF="vtnea100.htm">Who We Are</A>
|
<A HREF="vtnea200.htm">Opportunities for Educators</A> |
<A HREF="vtnea300.htm">Advice for Parents and Support for Kids</A></FONT></P>
<H1 ALIGN="CENTER"><BIG>Welcome To Vermont-NEA</BIG></H1>
<H1><IMG SRC="school4.jpg" ALIGN="right" HEIGHT="346" WIDTH="375"></H1>
<H2><A HREF="vtnea100.htm"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>
<A HREF="vtnea100.htm">Who We Are</A></H2>
<P>The Vermont-National Education Association is a voluntary membership
organization of 8,500 Vermont teachers and education support personnel.
Vermont-NEA serves its members' primary interests: children and education. </P>
<P>We welcome everyone who cares about education to our web site. Here we offer
fresh, constantly updated information to <I>support</I> the work of educators,
<I>encourage</I> the contribution of parents, and <I>nurture</I> the learning
of children and young adults.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><A
HREF="http://dol.state.vt.us/gopher_root3/000000/supct/a-e/brigham_v_state.96-502"><IMG
SRC="exclamat.gif" WIDTH="31" HEIGHT="64"></A>  In a decision that has profound
implications for every community, student, and educator in Vermont,
<A
HREF="http://dol.state.vt.us/gopher_root3/000000/supct/a-e/brigham_v_state.96-502">the
Vermont Supreme Court has ruled</A> that the state's current system of funding
education is unconstitutional.</P>
<H2><A HREF="vtnea200.htm"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>
<A HREF="vtnea200.htm">Opportunities for Educators</A></H2>
<P>Vermont educators are their own best professional resource.  Information
offered here was developed by educators, for educators.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"> <A HREF="court.htm"><IMG
SRC="newyelow.gif" WIDTH="75" HEIGHT="46"></A> The latest addition to this site
is a <A HREF="court.htm">message to Vermont-NEA local Association leaders</A>
about the momentous decision by the Vermont Supreme Court in the case of
Brigham, et al. v. State of Vermont.</P>
<H2><A HREF="vtnea300.htm"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>
<A HREF="vtnea300.htm">Advice for Parents and Support for Kids</A></H2>
<P>The teachers and education support personnel of Vermont-NEA developed these
resources for parents and school children.</P>
<P><A HREF="mailto:webmaster@vtnea.org"><IMG SRC="apple2.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>
  <B>About YOU!</B> We are very interested to know who is visiting our site and
what you think. Are you a parent? student? educator? surfer? citizen? all of the
above? Please e-mail your comments: <A HREF="mailto:webmaster@vtnea.org">webmaster@vtnea.org</A>
 </P>
<P>Vermont-NEA is located at 10 Wheelock Street in Montpelier, Vermont
05602-3737.  Phone: (802) 223-6375   Fax: (802) 223-1253.   The number of
visitors to the Vermont-NEA website since September 3, 1996: <B>2065</B>.   The
last website update: <B>February 11, 1997</B>.</P>
<P><I>About the artist:	Steve Barrows, an English teacher at Union-32 High
School in East Montpelier, created the art on this home page and on the pages of
the child's development calendar.</I></P></BODY></HTML>
