<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN//3.2">
<html>
<head>

   <TITLE>
RIT: COB: Finance
   </TITLE>

</head>

<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
<table width=590>
<tr>
<td>

	<!-- Start Header Information here -->
<center>
<IMG align=left  WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=98 SRC="../images/rit_tiger_small.gif" alt="RIT Tiger">



<IMG  WIDTH=375 HEIGHT=40 SRC="../images/banner_cob_medium.gif" alt="RIT's College of Business" border=0>
<br>
	<!-- Section Banner -->
<IMG  WIDTH=375 HEIGHT=35 SRC="../images/banner_degree.gif" alt="Section" border=0>
<br>
<br clear=all>
<hr noshade size="1">
</center>
	<!-- End Header Information -->

	<!-- Begin Page Content -->

<CENTER><H2>Finance</H2> </center>


<P>
The goal of the finance program is to produce graduates who will seek
solutions to the challenges and problems of modern business and who will
assume leadership in the ever-widening global environment.  Students are
taught the principles of financial decision making and given an
understanding of the complex economic, legal and financial environment in
which they operate.
<p>
Business leaders tell us that there us a need for managers with both
technical knowledge and communications skills.  Our curriculum trains
future managers who satisfy this need with a comprehensive understanding
of the world of business and its focus on Total Quality Management.
<p>
RIT's finance program provides a high level of technical professional
development through a comprehensive program of liberal arts,
communication and presentation skills, a solid business core and work in
the student's professional concentration.


<HR width="50%">
<CENTER><FONT size="+2">
<A HREF="finance_sequence.html">Course Sequence</A><BR>
<A HREF="finance_descripts.html">Course Descriptions</A><BR>
<A HREF="../faculty_staff/main_department.html#finance">Finance Faculty</A><BR>
</FONT>
<HR width="50%">
<P>


<TABLE width="80%" border=0 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=0>
<TR><TD><FONT size="+1"><STRONG>Required Courses</STRONG><BR>
</font>

Finance graduates will receive a bachelor of science degree in business
administration.  In addition to the required business core courses,
finance majors take six courses that compose the major, three required
courses and three elective courses.  Elective courses can be found in 
finance, accounting and economics.  The three required courses are:
<UL>
<LI><a href="finance_descripts.html#451">Valuation of real and Financial Assets</a>
<LI><a href="finance_descripts.html#452">Managing Corporate Assets and Liabilities</a>
<LI><a href="finance_descripts.html#453">Intermediate Investments</a>
</UL>



</TD></TR>

</TABLE>
</CENTER>



          <!-- End Page Content -->
<p>
