   <TITLE>
RIT: COB: Management Information Systems
   </TITLE>

</head>

<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
<table width=590>
<tr>
<td>

	<!-- Start Header Information here -->
<center>
<IMG align=left  WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=98 SRC="../images/rit_tiger_small.gif" alt="RIT Tiger">



<IMG  WIDTH=375 HEIGHT=40 SRC="../images/banner_cob_medium.gif" alt="RIT's College of Business" border=0>
<br>
	<!-- Section Banner -->
<IMG  WIDTH=375 HEIGHT=35 SRC="../images/banner_degree.gif" alt="Section" border=0>
<br>
<br clear=all>
<hr noshade size="1">
</center>
	<!-- End Header Information -->

	<!-- Begin Page Content -->



<CENTER><H2>Management Information Systems</H2> </center>
<P>
With the growing complexity of organizations and the increase in global
markets, information has become an extremely valuable asset.  Information
systems specialists create and manage the information resources required
for the success of today's organization.  As companies have learned to
make strategic use of such information to gain competitive advantage in
the marketplace, demand has grown dramatically for those who are trained
to design such systems.
<P>
RIT's information systems students receive an education in business,
computer programming and systems analysis with Total Quality Management
integrated throughout the curriculum.  Students also have a thorough
understanding of data processing fundamentals, including the ability to
write properly documented programs.  This combination ideally prepares
them to help design and create the types of computerized systems
businesses need.

<center>

<HR width=300>
<FONT size="+2">
<A HREF="infosys_sequence.html">Course Sequence</A><BR>
<A HREF="infosys_descripts.html">Course Descriptions</A><BR>
<A HREF="../faculty_staff/main_department.html#infosys">
Management Information Systems Faculty</A><BR>
</FONT>
<HR width=300>
<P>

<TABLE width="80%" border=0 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=0>
<TR><TD><FONT size="+1"><STRONG>Required Courses</STRONG><BR>
</font>
Information systems majors receive a bachelor of science degree in business administration.  In addition to business core courses, students take the following courses.
Required courses:
<UL>
<LI><a href="infosys_descripts.html#325">Fundamentals of Information Systems </a>
<LI>Introduction to Programming
<LI><a href="infosys_descripts.html#335">Information Systems Theory and Practice
</a>
<LI><a href="infosys_descripts.html#355">Information Technology Hardware and 
Software </a>
<LI>Business Applications--COBOL
<LI>Programming Elective
<LI><a href="infosys_descripts.html#363">Analysis and Logical Design </a>
<LI><a href="infosys_descripts.html#375">Network Technology </a>
<LI>Applied Database Management
<LI><a href="infosys_descripts.html#464">Analysis and Logical Design II </a>
<LI><a href="infosys_descripts.html#553">Project Management and Practice </a>
</UL>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>
          <!-- End Page Content -->
