<head>

   <TITLE>
RIT: COB: International Business
   </TITLE>

</head>

<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
<table width=590>
<tr>
<td>

	<!-- Start Header Information here -->
<center>
<IMG align=left  WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=98 SRC="../images/rit_tiger_small.gif" alt="RIT Tiger">



<IMG  WIDTH=375 HEIGHT=40 SRC="../images/banner_cob_medium.gif" alt="RIT's College of Business" border=0>
<br>
	<!-- Section Banner -->
<IMG  WIDTH=375 HEIGHT=35 SRC="../images/banner_degree.gif" alt="Section" border=0>
<br>
<br clear=all>
<hr noshade size="1">
</center>
	<!-- End Header Information -->

	<!-- Begin Page Content -->

<CENTER><H2>International Business</H2> </center>

<center><table border=0><tr><td> 

<P>
International competition in a global society has made passports
practically a necessity for U.S. business professionals.  Because
technology makes crossing international borders as easy as crossing the
street companies are becoming more international in focus.  Tomorrow's
corporate leaders will be those with expertise beyond the American
market.
<p>
With its theme of Total Quality Management, the international business
program at RIT prepares highly motivated students who want careers with an
international focus.  Our graduates satisfy the growing need for
managers, marketing specialists and financial analysts who understand the
values, structures and systems of the international marketplace.

</table></center>

	
<HR width="50%">
<CENTER><FONT size="+2">
<A HREF="international_sequence.html">Course Sequence</A><BR>
<!--A HREF="international_descripts.html"-->Course Descriptions<!--/A--><BR>
<A HREF="../faculty_staff/main_department.html#ib">International Business
Faculty</A><BR>
</FONT>
<HR width="50%">
<P>

<TABLE width="60%" border=0 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=0>
<TR><TD><FONT size="+1"><STRONG>Required Courses</STRONG><BR>
</font>

Students in this program receive a bachelor of science degree in business
administration with a major in international business and a co-major in
accounting, finance, information systems, management or marketing.  In
addition to the business core courses, which provide a full range of
business knowledge, international business students take the required
courses for both their major and co-major.  Two years of foreign language
are also a requirement.<br>
<br>
International Business majors select from the following courses:
<UL>
<LI><!--a href=international_descripts.html#-->Survey of International Business <!--/a-->
(Required)
<LI><!--a href=international_descripts.html#-->International Marketing <!--/a-->
<LI><!--a href=international_descripts.html#-->International Finance <!--/a-->
<LI><!--a href=international_descripts.html#-->International Management <!--/a-->
<LI><!--a href=international_descripts.html#-->International Accounting <!--/a-->
<LI><!--a href=international_descripts.html#-->Multinational Business Operations & Strategy<!--/a-->
<LI><!--a href=international_descripts.html#-->International Seminar <!--/a-->
</UL>

Co-Major course requirements:
<UL>
<LI>Four required/elective courses in accounting, finance, information
systems, management or marketing 
</UL>

</TD></TR>

</TABLE>
</CENTER>




          <!-- End Page Content -->
