   <TITLE>
RIT: COB: Marketing
   </TITLE>

</head>

<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
<table width=590>
<tr>
<td>

	<!-- Start Header Information here -->
<center>
<IMG align=left  WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=98 SRC="../images/rit_tiger_small.gif" alt="RIT Tiger">



<IMG  WIDTH=375 HEIGHT=40 SRC="../images/banner_cob_medium.gif" alt="RIT's College of Business" border=0>
<br>
	<!-- Section Banner -->
<IMG  WIDTH=375 HEIGHT=35 SRC="../images/banner_degree.gif" alt="Section" border=0>
<br>
<br clear=all>
<hr noshade size="1">
</center>
	<!-- End Header Information -->

	<!-- Begin Page Content -->
<CENTER><H2>Marketing</H2> </center>
<center>
<P>
With the growing emphasis on quality management and customer
satisfaction, the role of marketing is crucial to the goals of business
today.  The primary function of marketing is to understand the needs of
customers and to design a strategy that meets their needs in
product/service development, advertising and professional selling,
channel management and pricing.  RIT's marketing program excels in
teaching the future marketing professional to listen to the voice of the
customer.
<p>
More than 90% of employees recently surveyed indicated that an
understanding of quality principles is needed for success in business
today.  RIT's College of Business has received honors and national
recognition from employers as a leader in quality management education.

</center>

<HR width="50%">
<CENTER><FONT size="+2">
<A HREF="marketing_sequence.html">Course Sequence</A><BR>
<A HREF="marketing_descripts.html">Course Descriptions</A><BR>
<A HREF="../faculty_staff/main_department.html#marketing">Marketing Faculty</A><BR>
</FONT>
</center>
<HR width="50%">
<P>

<TABLE width="80%" border=0 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=0>
<TR><TD><FONT size="+1"><STRONG>Required Courses</STRONG><BR>
</font>
Marketing graduates receive a bachelor of science degree in business administration.  In addition to the required business core courses, marketing majors take six courses that compose the major:  four required courses plus two electives.<br>
<br>
Required courses:
<UL>
<LI><a href="marketing_descripts.html#505">Buyer Behavior and Satisfaction</a>
<LI><a href="marketing_descripts.html#551">Marketing Research</a>
<LI><a href="marketing_descripts.html#550">Marketing Management Problems</a>
<LI><a href="marketing_descripts.html#559">Professional Selling</a>
</UL>
Electives:
<UL>
<LI><a href="marketing_descripts.html#555">International Marketing</a>
<LI><a href="marketing_descripts.html#560">Marketing Communications</a>
<LI><a href="marketing_descripts.html#553">Sales Management</a>
<LI><a href="marketing_descripts.html#530">Marketing Channels</a>
<LI><a href="marketing_descripts.html#554">Marketing Seminar</a>
</UL>

</TD></TR>
</TABLE>


          <!-- End Page Content -->
