   <TITLE>
RIT: COB: Executive MBA
   </TITLE>

</head>

<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
<table width=590>
<tr>
<td>

	<!-- Start Header Information here -->
<center>
<IMG align=left  WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=98 SRC="../images/rit_tiger_small.gif" alt="RIT Tiger">



<IMG  WIDTH=375 HEIGHT=40 SRC="../images/banner_cob_medium.gif" alt="RIT's College of Business" border=0>
<br>
	<!-- Section Banner -->
<IMG  WIDTH=375 HEIGHT=35 SRC="../images/banner_degree.gif" alt="Section" border=0>
<br>
<br clear=all>
<hr noshade size="1">
</center>
	<!-- End Header Information -->

	<!-- Begin Page Content -->



<p>
<h2>The Executive MBA Program at RIT</H2>
<P>
The Executive MBA Program is designed to meet the needs of emerging
executives, particularly technical and functional specialists, in
organizations serious about improving customer satisfaction, product
quality, and organizational productivity. This curriculum is designed with
the expectation that students will have significant (generally eight
years) professional experience. This rich background contributes to a
higher level of group interaction than normally found in traditional MBA
programs.

<p>
The team responsible for developing this curriculum was evenly composed of
RIT faculty and senior executives from manufacturing and service
industries. This team developed an Executive MBA educational experience
that is cross functional, dynamic, and relevant for organizational leaders
of the 21st century.
<HR>
<center><table border=0 cellspacing=10>
	
<tr><td><a href="emba_curriculum.html">Curriculum</a></td>
<td> | </td><td><a href="emba_sponsors.html">Students and Sponsors</a></td>
</tr>
	
</table></center>
<HR>

RIT's Executive MBA will enable candidates to increase business results
and personal productivity. Participants in this unique program will:
<p>
<ul>
<li>develop <b> strategic perspectives </b> consistent with the needs of
various stakeholder
<li>Utilize the principles of <b> quality </b> and quality-based tools to
accomplish organizational goals
<li>Strengthen <b>leadership </b> and interactive skills by collaborating
with teams of professional peers and faculty
<li>Develop <b>strategic perspectives </b>consistent with the needs of
customers, stockholders, employees, the community, and other stakeholder
<li>Use <b>cross-functional </b> approaches to enhance analytical
abilities and decision making capabilities
<li>Obtain a <b>solid foundation</b> in the functional areas of business
</ul> 

The backbone of RIT's Executive MBA are the curricular topics relating to
strategic decision making, total quality and leadership. The integrity of
the MBA is maintained, while the content delivered is unique. Traditional
MBA topics, such as marketing, finance, and production management, are
designed to be delivered and discussed in an inter-disciplinary format.

<p>

Today's global manufacturing and service environments require executives
who possess skills different from those needed a few years ago. A stronger
focus on leadership, customer satisfaction, productivity, and a
world-class approach are essential to success.
<P>

Our Executive MBA was designed, by a team of RIT faculty and executives
from all sectors, for professionals with <EM>substantial career
experience.</EM> <br>

The program's strengths are strategic decision making, organizational
leadership, and Total Quality. Completion of the Executive MBA will enable
candidates to increase business results and their personal productivity.
<P>
<hr>

<H3>Key Features of the Executive MBA</H3>
<p>

Executive MBA students must have a minimum of eight years of professional
experience and be sponsored by their employers. Executive MBA courses are
conducted on alternate weekends--Friday and Saturday of each
weekend--during the academic year and will be completed within two years.
Executive MBA students work in teams, studying a curriculum that focuses
on developing top

management skills.
<P>

Quality Management Education transforms talented organizational
specialists into leaders for the 21st century. This program is ideal for
emerging executives in organizations serious about improving customer
satisfaction and product quality.
<p>

The traditional functional areas of business are not taught as distinct,
separate courses. Instead, they are integrated throughout the curriculum
as critical skills supporting effective implementation of quality-oriented
strategies.
<p>

The Executive MBA has been distinguished as a national "hands-on"
educational experience. It is a unique combination of the best theoretical
approaches stressing issues of implementation and utilization. It is a
"general management" approach to graduate business learning. 
<P>
<hr>
<H3>Admissions Requirement and Procedures</H3>
<p>

All correspondence for Executive MBA admissions information and
for the submission of required documents should be sent to:<P>
     Rochester Institute of Technology<br>
     Executive MBA Office<br>
     Max Lowenthal Building<br>    
     107 Lomb Memorial Drive<br>
     Rochester, NY 14623-5608<br>
     716-475-7435 (phone)<br>
     716-475-7055 (fax)<P>

<hr>
<p> 

<H3>Admissions Criteria</H3>
<p>

In order to be considered for admission to the Executive MBA
program, a candidate must:<p>
<ul>
<LI>have a minimum of eight years of professional experience and
hold advanced technical, managerial, or executive responsibilities;

<LI>be sponsored by his or her employer;
<LI>must have earned a bachelor's degree;
<LI>be interviewed by a representative of the Executive MBA team;
<li>submit a completed admissions package.
</ul>

<hr>
<p>

<H3><B>Program Methodology</B></H3>

<p>

Each candidate creates a personal development plan based on an assessment
of key leadership and interactive skills. Students are assigned to a
mentor who will work with each participant to accomplish his or her
individualized plan.
<p>

The Executive MBA faculty is composed of outstanding teaching
professionals, both from within and outside of RIT. They work as a team to
fully integrate the topics presented in the modules.

<p>

The curriculum is delivered using a cross-functional approach. Using this
method of learning enhances candidates' abilities to fully integrate the
topics presented in all modules. 
<P>
The curriculum is delivered using a cross-functional approach. Using this
method of learning enhances candidates abilities to work across functional
areas.
<p>

Each module includes theory, example, and application tools, with the
latest software being used to increase individual and organizational
productivity. Computers and electronic messages are used to connect
student team members and faculty between bi-weekly meetings.
<p>

A centerpiece of most weekends will be an integrating tool; e.g., case
studies, examples from sponsoring companies, and simulations. Some of
these cases are from applicants for the RIT/USA Today Quality Cup. Typical
cases will include large manufacturers, hospitals, service providers,
governmental

agencies, multinational firms, medium sized suppliers, and distributors.


