	<!-- End Header Information -->

	<!-- Begin Page Content -->


<center><h2>Master of Science in Finance</H2></center>
<p>

Rochester Institute of Technology's master of science degree in finance
will prepare students to specialize in the finance field. Our program
emphasizes depth in both theory and applications and will develop the
ability to address financial questions. The analytical, deductive nature
of the program is designed to create financial professionals who will be
adaptable to dynamic changes in the deregulated financial industry and its
dramatic growth in investment options.
<p>

For students seeking chartered financial analyst (CFA) certification this
program provides the ideal education preparation.
<p>


Courses may be completed in as little as one year by full-time students or
in 18 months by part-time students. The program can accommodate students
who have undergraduate degrees in business or in other fields.
<p>

The MS in finance prepares students for managerial careers in financial
institutions and in corporate finance, investment and in analysis and
portfolio management and financial consulting. The course parallel the
Chartered Financial Analyst programs that prepare students to take the CFA
exam.
<p> 

The master of science in finance program is designed to prepare students
for managerial careers in corporate finance, investment analysis and
portfolio management, financial consulting and financial institutions.
<p>

All candidates must also complete a comprehensive exam in Finance
before receiving their degree.
<p>

<center><b> Courses</b></center>
The MS differs from the MBA in that it concentrates on finance courses
rather than the span of electives offered by an MBA. Offering great
flexibility for employed professional, classes are scheduled for afternoon
and evening.
<p>

<dl>
<dd> Financial Accounting Systems<Br>
<dd> Statistical Analysis for Decision Making<br>
<dd> Economics for Managers<br> 
<dd> Microeconomics<br>
<dd> Financial Analysis for Managers<br>
<dd> Financial Management II <br> 
<DD> Securities and Investment Analysis<br>
<dd> Financial Institutions and Markets<br>
<dd> Two Finance electives<br> 
<dd> Two non-Finance business electives<br>
</dl>
<hr> 

<center><h3>Preparation for the CFA Examination</h3></center>
<p>

The degree was tailored with the input of finance professional with 
courses to parallel the course content of the chartered financial analyst
program. The prestigious CFA is a valuable option for students who choose
to embark on this career path. Certification also is required by many
employers for their financial specialists.
<p>

Select courses are taught by CFA's and the department has acted as the
upstate coordinator for the CFA exam for many years
<p>

<hr>
<center><h3>Curriculum</H3></center>
<p>
The MS in finance program of study consists of 48 credits earned through
nine required courses, three electives and a comprehensive field exam.
Introduction to Statistics and Graduate Math Review may be required as
prerequisite courses (4 credits) upon entrance into this program.




